Title: The Ironworks, Dundrum Town, Dundrum, Dublin 14
Description:
Introducing The Ironworks — Exceptional Rental Living in Dundrum Town

Savills is proud to present The Ironworks, a brand-new rental development located in Dundrum Town, Dublin's premier destination for shopping, dining, culture, and lifestyle. 
These beautifully designed homes offer the perfect blend of style and convenience, right in the heart of where everything is happening.

Key Features:

-	Property options: Choose from a selection of stylish Studio, 1-bedroom, and 2-bedroom
        apartments.
-	Onsite amenities: Enjoy a host of premium amenities including concierge services, a cardio gym,
        resident lounge, co-working space, MyPup parcel lockers, a spectacular rooftop garden, a private
        courtyard, and a dedicated private dining area.
-	Unbeatable location: Perfectly positioned in Dundrum Town one of Ireland's largest and most
        popular retail and leisure destinations. With over 100 shops, restaurants, cafés, a cinema, a 
        theatre, and green open spaces nearby — everything you need is just moments from your door.

Property Specifications:

-	Interior design: Each apartment is fully furnished with high-quality, bespoke furniture packs from
        Hyde Interiors, featuring contemporary finishes throughout.
-	Modern kitchen: Sleek, custom-designed kitchens fitted with premium appliances.
-	Luxury bathrooms: Main and ensuite bathrooms with elegant, high-spec fittings.
-	Outdoor Space: Enjoy your own private outdoor retreat with either a spacious balcony or a glazed
        winter garden. 
-	Parking & storage: Secure underground car parking and dedicated bicycle storage available.
-	Energy efficiency: All units are A2-A3 BER rated and the development operates fully electric, 
        ensuring excellent energy efficiency, lower emissions and long term comfort for residents. 

Transport & Connectivity:
The Ironworks is superbly connected — just a short walk to the Luas Green Line, with multiple Dublin Bus routes nearby. Dublin City Centre is easily accessible, making commuting quick and stress-free.

Viewings now available by appointment with Savills.

Come and explore The Ironworks — a meticulously designed development offering unrivalled rental living at the centre of Dundrum's vibrant lifestyle hub.


NOTE: The particulars detailed here are for the purposes of representing the development only. Visual representations, finishes, layouts and/or scales may be approximate or representative of the development rather than exact specifications of the actual unit. The landlord reserves the right to make alterations to the design and specification in the overall interest of the development. Amenities are delivered in line with the overall development programme and may open at different times to the apartment move-in dates. These timelines are indicative and subject to change.
Facilities: Cable Television, Central Heating, Co-working Space, Community Events, Concierge, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Gym, Internet, Microwave, Parking, Residents Lounge, Washing Machine

Title: Alta Verde, Blackrock, Cross Avenue, Blackrock, Co. Dublin
Description:
Alta Verde, operated by Domu, is a brand-new apartment development located in the highly sought-after area of Blackrock. Nestled among mature chestnut trees, the three architecturally designed apartment blocks are complemented by best-in-class amenities and offer spectacular views across Dublin Bay, the city skyline, and the Dublin Mountains.

Alta Verde blends coastal charm with modern convenience. Just minutes from the shoreline and well-connected to the city via DART and bus routes, these thoughtfully designed apartments offer a tranquil retreat with effortless access to everything Dublin has to offer.

At Alta Verde, urban living is reimagined. Enjoy premium amenities, stylish interiors, and a community-focused lifestyle. Residents have access to beautifully landscaped outdoor spaces, state-of-the-art fitness facilities, an on-site padel court, dedicated co-working areas, a stunning residents' lounge, rooftop terraces, and exclusive events — all designed to elevate your everyday life.

Discover living redefined — apply today and step into a living experience tailored for modern life.

To book a viewing visit: www.altaverde.ie
Facilities: Alarm, Central Heating, Co-working Space, Community Events, Concierge, Dishwasher, Dryer, Games/Entertainment Rooms, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Gym, Internet, Microwave, Parking, Pets Allowed, Residents Lounge, Washing Machine, Wheelchair Access

Title: Studio, Alta Verde, Blackrock, Cross Avenue, Blackrock, Co. Dublin
Description:

•	Fully furnished apartments with a choice of premium interior finishes

•	Contemporary fitted kitchens with solid surface countertops and integrated NEFF appliances, including oven, microwave, dishwasher

Title: 18 Newmarket Square, Dublin City Centre, Dublin 8
Description:
Discover a bold new chapter of city living at 18 Newmarket Square - where the heritage of Dublin's Liberties meets the buzz of one of the world's coolest neighbourhoods.

The Liberties is Dublin at its most authentic - a place where history, culture, and creativity collide. Once the centre of Ireland's brewing and distilling tradition, today it's alive with bustling markets, artisan cafés, boutique distilleries, galleries, and cultural landmarks. Wander through cobbled streets rich in character, explore local food stalls and independent shops, or enjoy a thriving nightlife scene - all just minutes from Grafton Street and the city centre.

Rising above this dynamic backdrop, 18 Newmarket Square brings a new dimension to urban living. The development blends striking modern design with the spirit of its historic surroundings, creating a home that's both contemporary and connected to its community.

Residents enjoy access to an exceptional range of amenities, including:

Gym & Wellness Centre - exclusively for residents.

Rooftop terraces with sweeping views of the Dublin Mountains and skyline.

Reception Lounge for a warm welcome.

TV lounge and games room for relaxation and socialising.

Superfast Wi-Fi, secure bike storage, and parcel collection.

At 18 Newmarket Square, you're not just moving into a home - you're stepping into a vibrant community in one of Dublin's most exciting neighbourhoods.

Photographs are for illustrative purposes, and as the unit layout may differ.
Facilities: Central Heating, Co-working Space, Concierge, Dishwasher, Dryer, Games/Entertainment Rooms, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Gym, Microwave, Residents Lounge, Washing Machine

Title: Studio , 18 Newmarket Square, Dublin City Centre, Dublin 8
Description:
Discover a bold new way of urban living at 18 Newmarket Square, right in the heart of The Liberties – recently named one of the world’s coolest neighbourhoods. Here, history meets modernity, charm blends with convenience, and community thrives. 


Get ready to make new friends, create unforgettable memories, and live your best life! Newmarket Square guarantees you the lifestyle upgrade you deserve!


18 Newmarket Square boasts a host first-class amenities for a lifestyle of comfort:

	Gym & wellness centre, free and exclusively for residents,
      Landscaped rooftop terraces with panoramic views of the city and Dublin mountains to 
        unwind, away from the nearby buzz of the city,
	Shared co -working space to ease the flexibility of working remotely,
	Reception Lounge 
	Cinema room to help you relax away from the bustle of the city,
	Seamless high-speed Wi-Fi connectivity,
	Games room with a variety of entertainment options for residents,
	Bike storage rooms
	Games room with a variety of entertainment options for residents.


You can explore the city  from our prime location and you are guaranteed to find:

	Neighbourhood distilleries, restaurants, cafes, and artist studios, 
	Trendy shops and landmarks plus live music venues,
	Excellent public transport links - Numerous bus stops and Luas stop on your doorstep, 
	Short walk to Christ Church Cathedral, Guinness Storehouse and St. Stephen's Green.

All apartments consist of:

	Spacious, light-filled space
       Stylish fully furnished, bespoke interior design
	A-rated development, energy efficient apartments
	Private balconies with stunning Dublin mountains and city views,
	Modern and contemporary apartments reaching the 9th floor,
	Open-plan kitchen, living, and dining area,
	Built-in wardrobes and ample storage,
	Main bathroom, en-suite bathroom in the main bedroom, 
	High-quality fixtures and finishes.

With a variety of apartment types and layouts available, you’re sure to find the perfect fit –Contact a member of our team today to arrange a viewing and see for yourself what 18 Newmarket Square has to offer.

Live the Dublin dream: Book your viewing today!

Title: Lime House, Sean Moore Road, Dublin 4
Description:
Welcome to Life in a New Light

Glass Bottle is a new kind of neighbourhood for Dublin, spanning over 37 acres. One shaped by the people who live and visit here. Designed for connection, built for progress, and rich with culture and experience, it brings together homes and social spaces in a way that feels seamless, modern and alive. 

Nestled between Dublin Port and Dublin Bay Glass Bottle gives you the opportunity to live within the city, combining innovation, creativity and culture with wellness, nature and the water. This is exciting and dynamic living in the city and by the bay.

Lime House at Glass Bottle, the first residential building consisting of 212 tastefully decorated A rated studio, 1, 2 and 3 bedroom apartments with state-of-the-art amenities including our residents' gym and fitness studio, cosy screening room, private dining room spaces, rooftop terraces, resident lounges, flexible co-working spaces, landscaped courtyard, resident events and more.

For more information or to book a viewing, please visit: www.glassbottle.ie
Facilities: Cable Television, Central Heating, Co-working Space, Community Events, Concierge, Dishwasher, Dryer, Games/Entertainment Rooms, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Gym, Internet, Microwave, Pets Allowed, Residents Lounge, Serviced Property, Washing Machine, Wheelchair Access

Title: The Carriageworks,, Dublin 1
Description:
**We are open for Viewings**

Viewing times shown above are for this week or please copy and paste this link into your browser to book a specific time slot: https://calendly.com/thecarriageworksdublin/general-viewing?month=2025-10

Alternatively please email cwenquiries@hmd.ie for other dates and times that suit you to come and visit us. 


For more information please visit : www.thecarriageworksdublin.ie

Welcome to The Carriageworks, Dublin's most exciting new address for modern city living. This landmark development offers a range of beautifully finished apartments and duplexes, each designed to provide comfort, style, and sustainability. Step inside and you'll find bright, open-plan, fully furnished interiors with high-quality appliances, smart heating controls, and elegant bathrooms. Every detail has been carefully considered to make life easy and enjoyable, from clever storage solutions to energy-efficient features.

Amenities at The Carriageworks:

Residents enjoy a host of amenities designed to enhance your lifestyle:
-	Rooftop Sauna & Ice baths: Relax and unwind with panoramic city views.
-	Contrast Hydro Showers: Refresh and energise after a workout or long day.
-	Rooftop Wellness area: Wellness spaces for mind and body.

Title: Claremont, Howth Road, Howth, Dublin 13
Description:
Experience the thrill of coastal living at Howth’s most prestigious new rental address – Claremont – Luxury Seafront Living. 

Visit ClaremontHowth.ie or apply below to schedule your viewing today!

Claremont: Luxury Seafront Living - Breathtaking Views in Howth’s Prime Location
This new residential development in the heart of Howth offers a modern luxury  lifestyle in a beautiful natural setting. Located close to the train station, Claremont is a 25 minute DART ride to the city centre and close to many other great towns along the north Dublin coast. Howth itself is a charming and picturesque village with a wide variety of cafés, restaurants, and shops at your doorstep, providing an idyllic setting for everyday living.

Luxury Apartments Finished to the Highest Standards
Prepare to live in luxury at Claremont, where every apartment is crafted to the highest standards, designed with a focus on quality, style and functionality to ensure your home is both stylish and practical. Featuring generous spaces, curated interiors featuring open-plan living areas that combine comfort and style, and floor-to-ceiling windows that flood the apartments with natural light while offering breathtaking sea views. 

First-Class Amenities for a Lifestyle of Comfort
At Claremont, luxury living isn’t just about the homes – it’s about a lifestyle. The development is professionally managed and offers an unrivaled array of first-class amenities, thoughtfully designed to enhance your lifestyle. Amenities include a 300 sq m professional standard fitness centre. Whether you're a fitness enthusiast or someone who prefers a more relaxed workout, the gym is fully equipped to cater to all your needs.

For those looking to unwind, the residents’ lounge offers a stylish and comfortable space to relax or socialise. Claremont also features coworking spaces, ideal if you prefer the flexibility of working remotely without sacrificing productivity. Landscaped courtyards provide peaceful spots where you can enjoy some fresh air, surrounded by nature’s beauty. And when it's time for some fun, the games room offers a variety of entertainment options for residents. 

Claremont: A New Standard in Coastal Living
Whether you’re seeking the perfect retreat from the hustle and bustle of city life or a vibrant community close to everything Dublin has to offer, Claremont offers the best of both worlds. It’s a place where every detail has been considered for your comfort, convenience, and enjoyment.
Sleep in your home – live in your building!

Not all the available properties and rents are listed here; please use those available at viewings. 2) The photos shown here may not be of the actual unit available but represent the standard of finish throughout the development.

Title: Grand Canal Harbour, Grand Canal Place, Dublin 8
Description:
Get ready to level up your lifestyle in the heart of Dublin's vibrant scene with these brand new apartments at Grand Canal Harbour, Dublin 8, at the Guinness Quarter, right by the James's Hospital Luas stop and buzzing Thomas Street. This isn't just any apartment - it's your ticket to a whole new way of living, where historic charm meets contemporary cool! Dublin 8 is one of only two postal districts to span the River Liffey. 

World Class designed buildings/apartments

Great connectivity - one can walk, cycle or get the Luas from here to any part of the city.

🏙️🎉 Ready to dive into one of the coolest neighbourhoods in the world? Time Out Magazine has spoken, and Dublin 8 is where it's at! With an electrifying mix of history, culture, arts and endless adventures, this is the place to be for those seeking a taste of Dublin's vibrant soul. From whiskey distilleries to trendy coffee shops, historic landmarks, and beyond, there's something here for every taste and vibe.

🌆 Stunning Views, Epic Vibes: Say hello to jaw-dropping views and Instagram-worthy interiors! Our finished apartment development at Grand Canal Harbour is all about spacious living and breathtaking panoramas. Imagine waking up to stunning cityscapes every day - that's the level of epic we're talking about!

🎉 Amenities for Days: Get ready to live your best life with a lineup of on-site amenities at Grand Canal Harbour that'll make every day feel like a holiday! We're talking co-working spaces, hip cafes, a killer gym, yoga studio, cinema, and even a games room with a putting green! And when you need to unwind, kick back in one of our resident lounges - your ultimate chill zone awaits!

Fully pedestrianised: Features at the Grand Canal Harbour development include extensive landscaped areas, including roof terraces, which have been designed to enhance biodiversity - it's a green oasis in the heart of the city with semi-open winter gardens to facilitate all year round and all weather use.

☕ Community Buzz, Your Way: Join a community that's all about good vibes and great times! With an on-site cafe, creche, and supermarket, you'll be living in a neighbourhood that's as convenient as it is cool. Get ready to make new friends, create unforgettable memories, and live your best life, all within walking distance of your front door!

🌿 Green Living, Cool Living: Go green without sacrificing style! Grand Canal Harbour, Dublin 8 is all about sustainability, so you can feel good about living in a home that's as eco-friendly as it is chic. Embrace a lifestyle that's as conscious as it is cool and join us in making a positive impact on the world!

🎸 Dublin Dreams Come True: Picture this - living right next to the legendary Guinness Storehouse, with Dublin's iconic landmarks as your backdrop. From historic castles to buzzing markets, Dublin 8 is the perfect mix of city living. 

🤝 Join the Movement: Be part of something big, something bold, something that's changing the game! This developer doesn't just build homes - they build communities. Get ready to be part of a tribe that's all about living life to the fullest and making every moment count! 

🚀Prime Location, Endless Adventures: Step out of your front door and dive into the beating heart of Dublin! From world-class pubs and trendy eateries to cultural hotspots and boutique shops, everything you crave is just a stone's throw away. Live where the action is and let Dublin 8 become your playground for urban exploration! With Phoenix Park, Europe's largest city park, close by, outdoor enthusiasts will find their paradise for walks, cycles, and maybe even a deer sighting or two! 

Old Charm, New Culture: Dublin 8 blends old-world charm with a hipster flair, boasting winding streets, antique shops, and hidden gems waiting to be discovered. It's a place where tradition meets innovation, offering something new around every corner.
Facilities: Cable Television, Central Heating, Co-working Space, Community Events, Concierge, Dishwasher, Dryer, Games/Entertainment Rooms, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Gym, Internet, Microwave, Parking, Pets Allowed, Residents Lounge, Washing Machine, Wheelchair Access
AgentAddress: O'Connell Bridge House,  27/28 D'Olier Street, Dublin 2 D02 RR99

Title: Rockpoint, Newtown Avenue, Blackrock, Co. Dublin
Description:
Rockpoint by Moran Living, Blackrock Village represents a best in class development, comprising of 91 residential units situated in a long established and desirable residential area overlooking Dublin Bay. The development comprises of one, two and three bedroom apartments that are designed and styled to the very highest of standards with A rated BERs. Rockpoint offers an exceptional living experience. Tenants of the this newly built development benefit from on-site maintenance and management services, landscaped outdoor communal areas and stunning sea views. The interiors are spacious, and light filled spread across two separate blocks ranging from ground to fifth floor.

For further information please visit: rockpointblackrock.com

The apartments are now available for immediate occupation and get in touch to arrange an appointment.

More about the location.

Located south-east of Dublin City, Rockpoint is situated in the affluent south Dublin village of Blackrock, a highly sought after residential area. The development benefits from close proximity to a number of easily accessible employment hubs and recreational amenities. Seapoint Dart Station is located less than a 5 minute walk from the property providing easy access into Dublin City Centre within 15 minutes, while a quality bus corridor is located on Rockpoint's doorstep. Additionally there are superb local shopping and leisure amenities in the nearby surrounding area, with newly refurbished Frascati Shopping Centre and Blackrock Centre including retailers such as the Marks & Spencer, Aldi & SuperValu located only a 5 minute walk away. Blackrock Park, Seapoint Beach and numerous sports facilities and leisure facilities are also within walking distance of Rockpoint.
Facilities: Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Parking, Washing Machine

Brickfield Square is the place to build your life around, with studio, one and two-bedroom apartments available. Private gardens, bike paths and thoughtfully designed children's play areas connect our community - creating a peaceful and vibrant place for friends and families.

At Brickfield Square, everything is at your fingertips. With a resident-first approach, all of our apartments are fully furnished, pet-friendly and designed for effortless living. Perfectly placed in Dublin 12, Brickfield Square borders the buzzing energy of Dublin 8, giving you access to some of the city's most exciting neighbourhoods. Just around the corner, Rialto and Inchicore are thriving with creativity, cafes and culture. TimeOut recently named Inchicore one of the world's coolest neighbourhoods, and when you experience the local charm, it's easy to see why.

You'll also be close to some of Dublin's best cultural and green spaces. Visit the Museum of Modern Art (IMMA), spend a sunny afternoon in Phoenix Park, or take care of life's essentials at the nearby Ashleaf Shopping Centre. And when it's time to enjoy a serene park space, St. Stephen's Green is only 3.6km away.

Explore the best of both worlds - tranquil parks, lively cafes, creative hubs and seamless connections. With so much variety only steps away, there's always something new to discover. Make space for the life you love at Brickfield Square.

The primary bedroom has an ensuite with a shower, while the separate bathroom has a bathtub. Our kitchen is fitted with modern appliances and splashback tiling as well as a breakfast bar. The north and south-facing windows fill the apartment with natural light.

Explore all that Brickfield Square has to offer, from vibrant local shops and eateries to tranquil parks and recreational spaces. With a wide range of public transport options just steps away, there's always something exciting to discover.

Enjoy 30 Days of Worry-Free Living with Our Peace of Mind Guarantee!
At Greystar, we care so much about the comfort and experience of our residents in their new home, and we are committed to providing you with the best rental experience in the market. If, for any reason, you feel we haven't met this promise, you can terminate your tenancy by providing 30 days' notice at any time within the first 30 days of your agreement. About the area:
Brickfield Square is just 3km from the city centre. Walk to the Luas at Suir Road in less than 10 minutes for direct access to the heart of the town, or take a bus to almost anywhere from Crumlin Road. Strategically located next to Brickfield Park, you can walk your dog in the green spaces of the park or take a stroll along the Grand Canal. Brickfield Square also is a stone’s throw away from Rialto village and Dunnes Stores at Crumlin Shopping Centre.

Description:
Dillon Marshall is proud to present Eglinton Place a prestigious collection of 1, 2, and 3-bedroom rental apartments nestled in the heart of Donnybrook, Dublin 4. This unique development offers a rare opportunity to experience serene urban living in a picturesque, leafy suburb, just steps away from the vibrant social hotspots and hubs of Ballsbridge, The Docklands, and Dublin City Centre. Residents at Eglinton Place will enjoy outstanding panoramic views of Dublin city, the coast and the Dublin Mountains from the apartments and rooftop terraces. This is a rare opportunity to lease in a prime city living within a serene, landmark development. With 148 high-quality apartments, each designed for comfort and style, Eglinton Place redefines urban living. Immerse yourself in the local culture with cafes, restaurants, parks like Herbert Park, and the scenic Dodder River Greenway just around the corner.
 
Features:
Panoramic Views: Enjoy breathtaking views of the majestic Dublin Mountains, Dublin city and the coast  from your apartment and the expansive rooftop terraces.
Convenient Access: Located within easy reach of Dublin's prime areas and vibrant social scene.

Title: O'Neill Court , Main Street, Belmayne, Dublin 13
Description:
Discover the Charm of O'Neill Court

Dillon Marshall Property Consultants proudly present O'Neill Court, an exclusive residential development nestled in the heart of Belmayne, Dublin 13. Offering generously sized 1, 2, and 3-bedroom apartments, this modern community combines elegant living spaces with an enviable location that caters to every lifestyle.

Prime Location and Exceptional Amenities
O'Neill Court offers unparalleled access to a wealth of local amenities, recreational facilities, and natural beauty. Residents will enjoy a tranquil private landscaped courtyard and gardens, complete with a children's play area and comfortable seating. Ground-floor apartments boast sun-filled private terraces, perfect for unwinding.

Located just 500m from Clarehall Shopping Centre and 3km from the coastline where you can enjoy coastal walks and quality time walking the Howth Harbour. Why not enjoy a round of golf at one of Irelands Premier Links Golf courses in Portmarnock Golf club. O'Neill Court provides easy access to a variety of retail, dining, and leisure options. Whether you're shopping for essentials, dining out, or seeking entertainment, everything you need is close at hand. Clarehall Shopping Centre offers a variety of stores, including Tesco Extra for groceries and household needs, Holland & Barrett for health products, and An Post for postal and banking services, making it a convenient spot for everyday errands.

Seamless Connectivity
Residents are well-connected to Dublin and beyond:
Clongriffin Train Station is only a short walk away.
Multiple bus routes are conveniently located on your doorstep.
Dublin Airport is a mere 15-minute drive, ensuring hassle-free travel.

Proximity to the Stunning Howth Peninsula
One of the standout features of O'Neill Court is its close proximity to Howth, a picturesque coastal village renowned for its scenic walking trails, vibrant seafood restaurants, and breathtaking views. Spend weekends exploring Howth Harbour, enjoying fresh catches, or embarking on the famous cliff walks with panoramic sea vistas.

Endless Recreational Opportunities

Rising from the 11th to the 20th floor, these exceptional luxury apartments offer a rare vantage point over Dublin 2, with sweeping views that take in the River Liffey, Trinity College, and the dynamic cityscape beyond. Title: Daneswell Place, Botanic Road, Daneswell Place, Botanic Road, Glasnevin, Glasnevin, Dublin 9
Description:
Daneswell Place is a new residential development in an enclosed cul-de-sac development in Glasnevin, Dublin 9. 

These new A-rated apartments are situated just over 2km from the city centre where residents will find city living at its best with numerous cafes, restaurants, bars, supermarkets and shops close by. 

Commuting or just a trip into town is simplicity itself. With walking to IFSC or town taking less than 25 minutes, and cycling even quicker, commutes don't come much more convenient. The area is very well served by public transport too. The Luas takes just 12 minutes from Phibsborough to George's Dock, plus there are also direct bus routes to the City Centre, Rathmines, Grangegorman and Donnybrook from the area or Drumcondra Train Station is a short walk away. If you are heading away, it's a mere 20 minutes (10km) drive from Daneswell Place to Dublin Airport.

All apartments are spacious and fully furnished to a high standard to include a large Smart TV to stream services. High-speed fibre broadband is included in the price for each apartment which is managed by our IT company to ensure there is little or no disruption.

Walking distance to buses, Luas and Drumcondra train station making for an easy commute. 

Heat recovery systems provide a continuous fresh clean filtered air supply for a dust and allergy-free environment for a healthier standard of living. Flexible terms with 12 months or longer agreements but only one month's notice is required if your circumstances change. 

Residents have a private or Juliet balcony, and all apartments have access to a private roof garden with fabulous views over Dublin. 

Car parking and storage for bicycles available.

Bus Services 
9 - to O'Connell Street, Broadstone, Mobhi Road, Charlestown 
83 and 83A - to Stannaway Ave, Lwr. Rathmines Rd, Wood Quay/Upr. Ormond Quay, Charlestown & Harristown

E2 - to Harristown, DCU, City Centre & Dun Laoghaire

38B - to Damastown, IBM, Aquatic Centre, Navan Road, Cabra Road, Mater Hospital, Berkeley Road & O'Connell Street (The Spire Of Dublin)

Title: The Burbidge, Lansdowne Place, Lansdowne Road, Dublin 4
Description:
Indoor/Outdoor sophisticated living. 
***Available January 2026***This luxurious three bedroom, two and a half bathroom duplex is accessible through its own door on the ground level.  The airy entrance hall leads upstairs to the primary en-suite with a deep-tubbed rain-shower spa bathroom and guest bedrooms that each contain a bed that can be converted to two singles from a king.  The guest bedrooms have access to their own spa bathroom.    The entry also leads downstairs to a half bath, and home office with adjacent child cubby or dog den, and open-concept living.   The living room, dining, and kitchen with a waterfall island and bar stools that make dining as comfortable as at the full dining table; is floor to ceiling double-paned soundproof glass and therefore light and airy. The doors open to outdoor space and a large furnished private terrace.  This luxe and beautifully appointed townhouse has upscale accessories, fine linens with down comforters, pillows, and throws, built-out laundry area and more that makes moving-in and enjoying effortless.  Broadband on two smart TVs and high speed are included. This brand-new home and has been lovingly fitted to be relaxing and…homey.  Lansdowne Place is one of the finest addresses in Dublin and is amenity-rich with a gym, treatment areas, conference room, and resident lounge. The concierge service is second to none.  The gated complex, Trinity College’s former botanical garden, boasts a large courtyard, beautifully maintained wild Irish gardens, and gorgeous water features. This letting comes with two parking spaces and additional storage in the car park.  More information can be found on these amenities at: https://www.lansdowneplace.ie/residents-amenities/
Facilities: Cable Television, Central Heating, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Parking, Pets Allowed, Washing Machine, Wheelchair Access

Title: Node D2 - Fitzwilliam Square, 25 Pembroke Street Upper, Dublin 2
Description:
Node D2 is Dublin's first curated living experience, where beautiful apartments and creative people come together to form inspiring luxury co-living! 

Our building is located on Dublin's stunning Georgian strip just off Fitzwilliam Square and has the perfect combination of historical references of the past with modern-day interior design. 

In our current times, privacy is paramount, and this is why all of our 2 & 3 bedrooms apartments have private dining/living areas where you can work, relax or have a good time with your flatmates. 

We have curated the design and décor of all our apartments - no two apartments look the same - so that you can enjoy a comfortable and functional home. Our high spec kitchens feature the famous retro SMEG fridges and our living rooms are uniquely furnished and showcase local artwork. 

The Rooftop Terrace is the perfect spot to catch some fresh air and enjoy the sunshine in the warmer months. 

Our Residents Lounge is the ideal place for catching up with your neighbours, and entertaining friends.

We invite you to become a part of the Node family, where every day is an opportunity for connection. 

Whether you're a professional, a creative spirit, or simply seeking a fresh start, discover your place in our vibrant community. Welcome home!
Facilities: Central Heating, Community Events, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Internet, Microwave, Residents Lounge, Serviced Property, Washing Machine

Title: Bedroom with a private bathroom, Node D2 - Fitzwilliam Square, 25 Pembroke Street Upper, Dublin 2
Description:
Room 101A is part of a 2-bedroom/ 2-bathroom apartment located on the First floor at the front of the building. 

The bright, stylishly appointed, spacious living room enjoys a quintessential Georgian City street view and features a funky (non-working) feature fireplace in the  living room. 

There is a large dining table, Smeg fridge freezer, and plenty of storage space in the kitchen.

You will share the living room and kitchen with one other tenant, currently a female, who has her own private room and bathroom. 

Room 101 A features a generous wardrobe, space for a small desk and a private non ensuite bathroom.

PLEASE NOTE:

* The bedroom is designed for SINGLE-OCCUPANCY-ONLY. 
* The monthly Utilities Charge covers Internet, Electricity, Gas, and Bin services. Housekeeping services are not included.


About Node Dublin: 

Node Dublin is situated on a stunning Georgian terrace in Dublin’s historic Georgian Quarter. With a mix of 23 stylishly appointed 2-bed and 3-bed shared apartments, it offers convenience and comfort at the heart of Dublin City.
In addition to their private apartments, Node residents can make use of our popular COMMUNAL SPACES, including our funky Rooftop Terrace and spectacular panoramic city views, breath-taking sunsets, and an exclusive Resident's Lounge/ Co-working Space.
We are super proud of the creative and diverse community we have created. We hope that you will come and join us.

Title: Mayor Square, Mayor Street Lower, IFSC, Dublin 1, Dublin 1
Description:
Located in the heart of Dublin's IFSC, Mayor Square offers well-equipped student accommodation with excellent transport links and easy access to universities, shops, and amenities. The residence provides a comfortable and secure living environment with modern facilities designed for both study and social life.

Room Options Available

- Twin En-Suite - €250 per week

Double-occupancy room with two single beds. Private en-suite bathroom shared between two. Fully furnished with a wardrobe, shelving, study desks, adjustable desk chairs, and a personal radiator. Shared kitchen and living space with 6-8 other residents
Room sizes range from 15m² - 18m²

Now accepting reservations for the 2025/26 academic year and semester 2 (January to June 2026). 41-week lease starting 23rd August 2025. Total rent: €10,250 (excluding service charges)

Deluxe En-Suite - From €301 per week

Single-occupancy bedroom. Private en-suite bathroom. Room sizes range from 12m² - 14m². Furnished with a single bed (1,900mm x 1,200mm), wardrobe, shelving, smart storage, blinds, study desk with light, adjustable desk chair, and personal radiator. Shared kitchen and living area with 6-8 other residents

2025/26 Academic Year:. Full-Year (41 Weeks) - €301 per week
Total rent: €12,341 (excluding service charges)

Semester 2 January to June 2026 (21 Weeks) - €320 per week


What's Included?

- Fixed utility charge (€35 per week) covering heating, hot water, WiFi, and waste disposal. 
- High-speed internet with up to 100Mb WiFi and 150Mb wired connection in rooms
- Fully fitted kitchen with an oven, grill, hob, microwave, fridge freezer, dishwasher, toaster, kettle, cookware, and utensils
- Parcel and delivery service at reception
- On-site laundry facilities (local charge applies)
- Maintenance team available for repairs and assistance
- Secure entry with keyless access and 24/7 CCTV monitoring
- Bike storage available

Location and Transport Links
Walking distance to:

- National College of Ireland - 1 minute
- Tesco Express - 3 minutes
- Trinity College Dublin - 21 minutes

By bike:

- Trinity College Dublin - 7 minutes
- Mater Hospital - 10 minutes
- Royal College of Surgeons Ireland - 12 minutes

By public transport:

- Temple Bar - 11 minutes
- Trinity College Dublin - 14 minutes
- Dublin Airport - 19 minutes

How to Secure a Room
To book a room, complete the reservation form. Once your application is received, a tenancy agreement will be issued. A €150 booking fee is required to confirm the booking. One month before arrival, an additional payment equal to one month's rent plus the utility charge will be due. Rent payments are then made on the 1st of each month. A refundable deposit of €500 is also required. 

For more information or to arrange a viewing, get in touch with StudnetHouse today.
Facilities: Central Heating, Dishwasher, Dryer, Internet, Laundry, Microwave, Washing Machine, Wheelchair Access

Title: East Wharf, East Wall Road, Dublin 3
Description:
**Available Now**

Welcome to East Wharf 

Discover East Wharf, a brand-new development offering contemporary apartments in the heart of Dublin 3's thriving East Wall neighbourhood. These apartments are designed to support a vibrant urban lifestyle, combining convenience, comfort, and community all in one exceptional location. 

Stylish, Spacious Apartments East Wharf apartments are thoughtfully designed to suit the needs of modern renters. Each home is crafted with high-quality finishes, contemporary fixtures, and spacious layouts that maximize light and space. 
Each apartment comes with: 

-Modern kitchens equipped with quality appliances, perfect for cooking and entertaining 

-Spacious living areas designed for relaxation and gatherings 

-Bedrooms with ample wardrobe space and natural light 

-Elegant bathrooms featuring high-quality fixtures and finishes 

- Exceptional Amenities for an Elevated Lifestyle East Wharf residents enjoy a range of exclusive amenities designed to make daily life easier and more enjoyable: 

- On-Site Gym: Keep fit without leaving home with a mix of gym equipment. 

- Residents Lounges: Perfect for work, studying, or simply relaxing with neighbours in a productive atmosphere. 

- Rooftop Garden: Unwind with views over Dublin, an excellent spot to relax, socialize, or enjoy a quiet moment. 

Prime Location in East Wall, Dublin 3 Located in one of Dublin's most connected neighbourhoods, East Wharf offers easy access to key areas in the city. You're just minutes from the Docklands and IFSC, putting you close to some of Dublin's top business, retail, and entertainment areas. The property is well-served by public transportation, including the DART and several bus routes, ensuring that the entire city is within reach. 

East Wall is a lively area known for its vibrant mix of cafes, shops, and parks. Nearby, you'll find the scenic Fairview Park, ideal for morning runs or weekend walks, and The Point Square for shopping, dining, and entertainment. Grocery stores, gyms, and other essential services are within easy reach, making daily life simple and convenient. 

East Wharf ..The Home You've Been Looking For Experience the perfect blend of modern design, lifestyle amenities, and an unbeatable location. Make East Wharf your new home and embrace the best of Dublin 3 living.

Title: The Lookout , Harbour Road, Dalkey, Co. Dublin
Description:
The Lookout, Harbour Road in South Co Dublin is a residential development of modern apartments overlooking Dalkey Island. Inspired by Dalkey's historical terraces, these two apartment buildings offer unrivaled views, chic design and convenient commuting to Dublin city centre in just 30 minutes.

Home to artists, writers, and musicians, Dalkey has a rich cultural heritage and vibrant community, and is filled with artisan boutiques, bustling cafés, and award-winning restaurants. While stunning coastal walks, yacht clubs, sports facilities, schools, and parks nearby offer activities for all ages.

We have a stunning one bed apartment available to rent in this beautiful development. 

Spacious, sustainable and elegant, the design of these bright and airy apartments reflect their coastal location. Each home includes a variety of enviable features including:

-	BoConcept styling and furniture 
-	Floor to ceiling large windows
-	Large open plan living 
-	Large balconies with sea and landscape views 
-	NEFF and Miele appliances 
-	Generous storage areas
-	Integrated kitchens with quartz counter tops
-	Utility room with separate washing machine and dryer
-	Fully tiled bathrooms
-	Built in wardrobes
-	Video intercom 
-	Excellent A2 / A3 energy rating 
-	Underground parking 
-	Secure bicycle storage

Set in beautifully landscaped gardens, all apartments have balconies with the majority offering views of the sea and surrounding landscape.

Designed to anticipate residents' needs they come complete with a range of fantastic amenities.

-	Exclusive residents' gym
-	Residents' work hub
-	Concierge service
-	Residents' lounge
-	Kitchen and dining area 
-	MyPup parcel management 
-	Pet friendly options 
-	Landscaped gardens

For more information, contact us to arrange a viewing

Title: Station View , The Crossings , Adamstown, Co. Dublin
Description:
Station View is a brand-new residential development consisting of Studio, 1, 2- & 3-bedroom apartments and duplexes located at "The Crossings" Adamstown.  The scheme is excellently positioned adjacent to Adamstown train station, which has a peak journey time of 12-minutes to Heuston Station. This new destination includes an array of amenities and services to support residents in their new homes and community.   

Station View is part of "The Crossings" development with a superb offering of spacious apartment types which are expertly designed to cater for all needs of today's lifestyles. Consisting of a range of layouts and unit types, the key features include modern kitchen, living room with spacious balcony, bedrooms with fitted wardrobes and master ensuite, separate utility room and an abundance of storage.   

The key features include. 

-	High Quality Modern Apartments
-	"Nordmende" Appliances
-	Bespoke Fit Out 
-	Spacious Layouts
-	Storage Rooms
-	Separate Utility Rooms
-	All bedrooms with fitted wardrobes and storage 
-	Well designed and maintained secure landscaped grounds. 
-	Large private terraces or balconies
-	A2 Rated

The interiors have been tastefully designed by Total Fitout Interiors.

The development also offers a range of onsite shared amenities and services which include:

-	Parcel Collection 
-	Lounge Area
-	Kitchen / Dining Room
-	Business Centre 
-	Games Room
-	Communal space

The Crossings" as a destination includes a significant retail amenity, Tesco, Aldi, a new three-acre public park.This, combined with a host of childcare, primary and secondary schools, ensures that Station View residents have all that they need on their doorstep. 

It is a short distance from the N3 and M50 Motorways, providing easy access in and out of Dublin City Centre and further afield for people travelling by car. The development is also close to a host of key employment hubs including Grange Castle and Park West Business Campus' as well as Intel Leixlip. There are also regular bus services to "The Crossings" with the 25B and 25 D bus / terminus just minutes' walk away. 

Register your interest now to arrange a viewing to be part of this exciting new community

Title: Walled Garden , Wyckham Way , Dundrum, Dublin 16
Description:
Visit www.walled-garden.ie for more details. 

The homes at Walled Garden sit in a large, landscaped haven. Each of the four apartment buildings feature a communal roof garden, offering ample outdoor space with stunning views of the locality, the city, and the Dublin mountains. There is an array of apartment layouts to choose from in Walled Garden and all apartments are pet friendly (T&C's apply). 

Walled Garden amenities have been designed to take up residence in a meticulously restored farm building dating back to the 1830s. This has been considerately transformed to become the amenities centre where it now houses a concierge area, residents' media room and a gym. There is also an outdoor gym, intimate seating courts, a play area and pond feature, bringing the overall sense of openness right to the heart of Walled Garden. Viewing is highly recommended to really appreciate the uniqueness of this one-of-a-kind development in the heart of Dublin's South Side.  

PLEASE NOTE: NO PARKING AVAILABLE ONSITE

The 1-bed apartments at Walled Garden are tastefully designed and laid out with a high-quality fit-out and furniture package.  The kitchens are fully fitted with Whirlpool dishwasher, oven/grill, hob, microwave and refrigerator and the utility room houses the washing machine/dryer, giving you extra space in your living area.  
The dining area is fitted out with table and chairs and extends to a generous living space with a large couch and coffee table with a balcony accessed from this room giving additional outdoor space. The balcony area is dressed with additional table and chairs and provides stunning views over the City or Mountains behind. 
The large bedroom has a double bed and built-in wardrobes to ensure more than enough storage with additional space. There is a large private bathroom with bath / shower and heated towel rails. 
There is there is limited parking available at an additional cost. T&Cs apply.
Facilities: Cable Television, Central Heating, Dishwasher, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Pets Allowed, Washing Machine

Title: Green Acre Grange , Upper Kilmacud Road , Dundrum, Dublin 14
Description:
Dubliv is delighted to present Green Acre Grange to the rental market, located adjacent to Airfield Estate in the heart of Dundrum. 

Green Acre Grange is a meticulously designed, generously proportioned, residential development offering fully furnished one-, two- and three-bedroom apartments, styled with intention, benefiting from large-glazed windows to maximise daylight, creating a real sense of connection to the outdoors. 
Strategically placed among a series of linked gardens, play arears and green spaces, the three buildings, ranging in height from five to eight stories, will benefit from green roofs providing a high-quality and sustainable living environment to support our residents' lifestyles.

The development boasts state of the art on site resident's amenities, making Green Acre Grange a self-contained urban oasis catering to all its residents' needs.
Our dedicated on-site property management team is on hand to tend to residents' requests, maintenance and to manage private amenity bookings and more.

Green Acre Grange residents' benefit from the following amenities:
-	Private gym
-	Bookable cinema room
-	Resident's lounge area 
-	Communal kitchen 
-	Games area
-	Business centre
-	Children's playroom
-	Top Brewer coffee station
-	Landscaped gardens 
-	Bike storage 
-	Children's Playground

Please note -This development does not have car parking space available.

Transport services are in plentiful supply with Balally Luas stop and the M50 in close proximity, our residents will stay well connected and travel with ease. 
Residents can enjoy instant access to Dundrum Town Centre, Grafton Street, Ranelagh, Sandyford and Cherrywood. Restaurants and cafes abound, schools and medical facilities; the renowned Mill Theatre, Marlay Park is close by, and the Dublin Mountains are escapable-to in mere minutes.

**Please note there are multiple unit types available in this development. The marketing material may not be of the exact unit available but represent the standard of finish. The rent advertised represents the starting rent for these property types. Rents will vary throughout the development depending on the specific unit type. The overall BER Rating at this development is A Rated, an individual BER cert for your specific apartment is available upon request, at move in.
Facilities: Alarm, Cable Television, Central Heating, Co-working Space, Community Events, Concierge, Dishwasher, Dryer, Games/Entertainment Rooms, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Gym, Internet, Microwave, Residents Lounge, Washing Machine

Title: Glenamuck Manor , Glenamuck Road, Dublin 18
Description:
Dillon Marshall is proud to present Glenamuck Manor, a stunning development of 1st Let One and Two-Bedroom Apartments, located off the Glenamuck Road connecting Enniskerry, Kilternan and Stepaside with the M50, Carrickmines, Foxrock, Dundrum and the city centre. This is a very accessible location in a highly sought after area of South Dublin. 

An idyllic combination of village life, city living and scenic surroundings, Glenamuck Manor offers excellent transport links, schools, shopping, dining and leisure facilities in abundance. Transport options include a nearby QBC bus corridor with Aircoach giving easy access to the city centre and airport. 

Glenamuck Manor is also within walking distance of the LUAS and its park and ride facility, connecting you to the City in 30 minutes. Ideally situated between Kilternan and Carrickmines and just a short drive from the business centres of Sandyford and Cherrywood. Enjoy a visit to the coast in nearby Dún Laoghaire, Dalkey and Killiney or a day out in the Dublin and Wicklow mountains all just 20 minutes away by car.

These stylish new homes come fully furnished and offer perfect convenience in a popular and well-established area, all within easy reach of Dublin City Centre. Simply turn the key and move in and immediately enjoy the comfort and security that Glenamuck Manor offers.

Homes at Glenamuck Manor are designed to support our residents' lifestyles, with modern finishes, open-plan layouts and private outside space. Curated interior options with sleek and contemporary furnishings maximise space, ensuring a seamless flow between areas. Description:
MD Property on behalf of Haven Homes is proud to present Manor Villas, a collection of newly renovated and beautifully styled 3 and 4 bedroom apartments in the quiet and highly sought after neighbourhood of Mount Argus Grove.

Bright and modern throughout, these luxurious apartments offer open concept living areas, updated kitchen and bathroom, and stylish furnishings. 

Mount Argus Grove is a peaceful and well-established residential area in Dublin 6W, ideally located near Harold's Cross, Terenure, and Kimmage. Pet friendly.

Title: Knockrabo, Mount Anville Road, Goatstown, Dublin 14
Description:
Set amongst exquisite parkland and positioned on a stunning elevated site, Knockrabo is a truly impressive development with 2 bedroom aparments available to let. 

Located in Goatstown and adjacent to Mount Anville School, Knockrabo has a host of services and amenities nearby to support any resident looking to reside in this beautiful location. There are 13 schools as well as Dundrum and Stillorgan Shopping Centre's within a 5km radius. 

Knockrabo is fully serviced by a variety of transport options. It is a 20min walk to the N11, main Stillorgan road which has an abundance of bus services that include the 76, 70, 46A ,155 & 115. The Green Luas Line is located at Sandyford just a 20-minute walk away also. Sandyford Industrial Park as well as access to the M50 are also within very close reach of the development. 

The apartments and penthouses have been thoughtfully designed with bright, spacious, well-proportioned rooms and large floor to ceiling windows, highlighting the incredible views over Dublin Bay and the city. The apartment blocks boast extremely high specification both internally in the units and common areas & externally on the finishes. 

Some of these features include: 
-	High-quality interior design finish and bespoke furniture pack
-	Arena-designed kitchens with top of the range appliances (Neff, Miele & Bora Extraction Hob) 
-	Luxury bathrooms and en suites
-	Separate utility room with ample storage
-	Generous balconies / terraces
-	Floor to ceiling windows
-	Excellent energy rating A2-A3
-	Hot water on demand
-       Underfloor Heating
-	Video intercom
-	Underground Parking
-	Storage Lockers 

If you need more spacious accommodation or simply looking to live in a more tranquil setting while still being close to all amenities Dublin City and County has to offer, Knockrabo is the perfect location to offer this beautiful mix of lifestyle.
Facilities: Cable Television, Central Heating, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Parking, Washing Machine

Title: Citywest Quarter, Citywest, Citywest, Co. Dublin
Description:
**One-bedroom apartment available**
**No Parking**

Located in the heart of Citywest, the complex is really well served with public transport - the Luas Red Line Citywest stop is right on your doorstep and runs every 10 minutes to both the City Centre and Tallaght. There are also numerous bus routes available on Citywest Road - Routes 65b, 77a & 175.
 
The apartment complex has been created with U in mind offering a range of expertly designed and constructed spacious apartments that cater for all the needs of today. The interiors have been tastefully designed by Ventura Living and are fitted with bespoke U furniture. The kitchens are fitted with hi-spec integrated Electrolux appliances. The generously proportioned light-filled living-rooms boast a private balcony overlooking the courtyard and landscaped grounds. The upper floors enjoy stunning views of the Dublin mountains. All the apartments are designed with energy efficiency in mind and are A-rated - residents will benefit from reduced heating bills.

U Citywest Quarter includes a really attractive residents amenity space which includes a multi-function  activity room. The bustling Citywest shopping centre, which includes a large Dunnes Stores and much more, is literally across the road.

To ensure everything runs smoothly in your new home in Citywest Quarter, the dedicated team at U by Urbeo, including an on-site manager, are on hand to assist in your management and maintenance queries. U Citywest Quarter also features a on-time parcel-management service.

Citywest has plenty of school and childcare options (including crèches) for its residents. These include a new primary school, Scoil Aoife, a short walk from Citywest Quarter and there are two other schools close by - Citywest & Saggart Community National School and Citywest Educate Together National School.

***Our team will endeavour to respond to all enquiries. However, this may not be possible in all cases due to the high volume of interest for the property and we wish you all the best with your property search.***

Title: Castle Walk, Castle Way, Cherrywood, Co. Dublin
Description:
**Located only a 5 minute walk from Laughanstown Luas Stop in Cherrywood via a new walkway**

Located in Cherrywood, Ireland's newest neighbourhood in South County Dublin, these brand new, fully furnished homes are ready to move in now.   

Designed for the rental market, these are very generously sized 2, 3 and 4 bedroom houses, 2 bedroom apartments and 3 bedroom duplexes all with ample parking, houses have gardens which are fitted with artificial grass.  The homes boast an A3 BER energy rating, which is achieved via zone-controlled heating and air-to-water heat pump systems, whose excellent efficiency keep utility costs to a minimum.  

There is an abundance of transport options and recreational activities nearby.  whilst the surrounding neighbourhoods offer shops (including Carrickmines shopping centre), cafes, restaurants and supermarkets with a variety of schools, parks and sports facilities.  

Cherrywood is located in south county Dublin, positioned to enjoy superb connection to the rest of the city and beyond via the LUAS Green Line, the M50 and the N11.  Cherrywood is also a mere fifteen minutes from the wilds of both the coast and the Dublin mountains, which provide stunning views and a true sense of calm; meanwhile, the bustling city is only 30 minutes away by LUAS. The houses are withing walking distance of The Cherrywood LUAS stop connecting you to the rest of Dublin in minutes. 

The nearby parks - Tully, Beckett and Kilbogget Park are all walking distance away.  Cabinteely Park and village is a little further on and just beyond that, the seaside delights of Dun Laoghaire, Killiney and Sandycove await. There are multiple golf courses and sports and leisure clubs dotted all around the area not to mention the abundance of Mountain trails and walks.

Description:
**Located only a 5 minute walk from Laughanstown Luas Stop in Cherrywood**

This is a large light filled 2 bedroom house with its own garden and space for 2 cars to park. 

The main hallway leads to a bright kitchen and dining area with doors to the back garden. 

The kitchens are German-made, contemporary in design and are supplied and fitted by Kube Kitchens.  They are elegantly finished with quartz work surfaces sitting atop sleekly built-in appliances including integrated NEFF fridge-freezer, oven, dishwasher, microwave, induction hob and Zanussi combo washer/dryer. 
  
This kitchen area opens out to a large dining area, perfect for parties or as an intimate setting.  
There is a dedicated utility room for added storage and the ground floor is completed by a separate, very spacious and cosy sitting room and a downstairs bathroom.  

Upstairs, the bedrooms are again large and flooded with natural light.  At night, they can become cosy, low-lit sanctuaries of quiet.  The principal bedroom includes an en-suite bathroom, equipped with a large shower and heated towel-rails.  The main upstairs bathroom is finished with stylish contemporary sanitary ware. 

Viewing is highly recommended. 

Cherrywood is located in south county Dublin, positioned to enjoy superb connection to the rest of the city and beyond via the LUAS Green Line, the M50 and the N11.   

Castle Walk itself is a five-minute walk from Laughanstown LUAS station, linked via a dedicated walkway, giving superb access to nearby amenities and further afield: 20 minutes to Dundrum Town Centre, 30 minutes to the city centre.  Castle Walk is also a mere fifteen minutes from the wilds of both the coast and the Dublin mountains.  These provide stunning views and indeed excellent refuge for an evening or weekend walk. 

The nearby parks - Tully, Beckett and Ticknock are all walking distance away.  Cabinteely village is a little further on and just beyond that, the seaside delights of Dun Laoghaire, Killiney and Sandycove await.

Title: St. Marnocks Bay, Portmarnock, Portmarnock, Co. Dublin
Description:
Located right in the heart of Portmarnock community beside the Dart Line, these  spacious, fully furnished purpose-built apartments and duplexes are available to move in.
 
Designed for the rental market, these new generously sized own door duplexes and apartments offer residents a welcoming home in a well-connected coastal location. With the sea a mere walking distance away, this development provides a tranquil setting away from the pressures of modern life. 

These properties boast an A3 BER energy rating, which is achieved via zone-controlled heating and air-to-water heat pump systems, whose excellent efficiency keep utility costs to a minimum. In addition, a bespoke furniture package is provided with high end interior design finishes and modern appliances. 
 
This development offers residents the options of extra large, new 2-bedroom apartments or 3 bedroom duplexes. Each residence offers own door secure access, large light filled entrance ways leading to a modern kitchen with integrated appliances, separate large living area, supplied with wifi/cable connectivity options, spacious modern main bathroom with bath and shower, large double bedrooms with one ensuite. Each living area offers a balcony to allow for private outdoor space and extra light. Nestled between the beautiful villages of Malahide and Howth, beside the sea and on the Dart, this stunning coastal location is blessed with great transport links and a wide range of excellent amenities. 

-	Portmarnock Dart Station is a short walk from the development and provides an excellent service with regular Dart service to the city, Connolly Station is a 20 minutes journey. 
-	Dublin Bus is also a short walk away from the scheme connecting you to Stephens Green (35 minutes), Dublin Airport (10 minutes) and nearby Malahide Village in minutes.
-	Dublin Airport is a short 15 minute drive away giving you easy and quick access for any of your travel needs as well as a quick connection to the various business hubs supported by the Airport.
-	The M50 is a mere 10 minute drive which connects to the motorways of Ireland. There is a dedicated cycle path from Portmarnock to the nearby village of Baldoyle and onwards to the famous fishing village of Howth.

** 4 Bedroom House** 

Located in a bustling North Dublin Seaside community right on the Dart Line. St. Marnocks Bay is situated in Portmarnock beside the sea on the DART line. Portmarnock is an attractive welcoming location, nestled between the beautiful villages of Malahide and Howth with great transport links and a wide range of excellent amenities for all ages in a stunning coastal setting. 

Portmarnock Village offers an array of shopping and dining options with a Lidl, Dunnes Stores and  other smaller local shops, cafes and pubs. Title: Adamstown, Lucan, Lucan, Co. Dublin
Description:
Purpose built, extra-large apartments located right in the heart of Adamstown, an established lively and vibrant community, with an excellent choice of schools, large public parks, sports and recreation clubs and retail all within the immediate vicinity. 

These spacious apartments offer residents a welcoming home in a well-connected location that puts quality of life at its core whilst also offering green open spaces within walking distance for numerous leisure activities, recreation and a tranquil setting away from the pressures of modern life. 

With excellent transport links within walking distance, Adamstown is within easy reach of Dublin City centre by train, bus or car  and is a location set up for all modern needs.

Adamstown Train Station is only a 5 minute walk from the development and provides an excellent service with regular trains to the city, stopping at Park West, Heuston Station, Dublin Connolly, Dublin Pearse, then on to Grand Canal Station. 

Regular buses between Adamstown and Dublin City offer an easy commute to the city centre with the 25B and 25D bus stops just minutes walk away from the development. 

Dublin Airport is only 20 minutes' drive whilst  the M4 road network enables immediate access for motorists to the city and the M50 Motorway, providing links to all major routes.

All homes in Adamstown have been designed with the resident in mind including bespoke furniture package, high end interior design finishes, and modern appliances. 

Adamstown offers residents the options of extra large 1 and 2 bedroom apartments. Each residence offers a large light filled entrance ways leading to a modern kitchen with integrated appliances, separate large living area, supplied with wifi/cable connectivity options, spacious modern main bathroom with bath and shower, large double bedrooms with one ensuite. Title: U HX, Harolds Cross Road, Dublin 6W
Description:
**First Floor 1-bed apartment available**

U by Urbeo is proud to present UHX, a brand-new residential development located in the heart of Harold's Cross. All homes in the development are "A" rated, meaning residents will enjoy comfort and warmth all year round. Ample storage is provided in all unit types, with generous storage spaces throughout. All apartments are fully fitted with high-end Danish and Italian joinery curated for UHX by MJF Interiors. 

This scheme has been created with U in mind offering a range of expertly designed and spacious apartments that cater for all the needs of today's lifestyles. Just a short stroll into Harold's Cross town centre or nearby Rathmines, Portobello & Terenure where you will find trendy cafes, bars and restaurants.

Ideally located with Dublin City Centre being easily reached by bike, bus, Luas or car. Bus stop at your doorstep with Dublin Bus routes include 9, 16, 49, 54a and 83 (the 16 bus makes its way to the airport). There is also a dedicated Nitelink service, the 49n, which serves the area.

At UHX you can take your pick of schools. There are three main secondary schools: Terenure College, St Marys Secondary School and Our Lady's School.

There is also plenty within the area to keep younger kids active. From Harold's Cross Youth Football Club, CYM Tennis Club, CYM Bowling Club to Bushy Park Running Club there is something for everyone.

Title: Parkleigh, Seven Mills, Parkleigh, Seven Mills, Dublin 22
Description:
Applications can only be made through our website: www.respond.ie/cost-rental

Respond, an Approved Housing Body and service provider, are delighted to offer cost rental homes at Seven Mills, Co. Dublin. This new type of rental accommodation is supported by the Department of Housing, Local Government and Heritage, the Housing Finance Agency and South Dublin County Council. 

For information on eligibility and how to apply for a cost rental property, PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE www.respond.ie and see our cost rental page www.respond.ie/cost-rental

THE CLOSING DATE FOR EXPRESSION OF INTEREST IS 05/12/2025 at 9am. Applicants selected to proceed are drawn by lottery. You will contacted if you are successfully selected through the lottery process.


The development comprises of 2, 2-bedroom apartments.

The monthly rate will be: €1,608.75/month

A deposit of €1558.75 (2 bed) is required per unit.

There will be an additional monthly charge of €21.66 for each unit in this development for refuse services.

Parkleigh Seven Mills

Parkleigh is the first neighbourhood in Seven Mills, the new town in Dublin 22. The development is set in 225 acres of green spaces and parkland, on the banks of the Grand Canal. Title: Elmville , Harolds Cross Road, Harolds Cross, Dublin 6W
Description:
Elmville is a stunning new development in Harold's Cross, a much sought-after address on Dublin's south side. Beginning at the Robert Emmet Bridge on the Grand Canal and only a 20-minute walk from the city centre, Harold's Cross is a lively and bustling suburb with an excellent public transport service.

Elmville fits right in with the energy and vibrancy of Harold's Cross. Inside the private gated development, the structural design utilises wood and exposed brick, marrying beautifully with its surrounding communal green landscape.

All apartments are large and enjoy a flood of natural light through floor-to-ceiling sliding doors, leading on to a private balcony or patio area. What makes this development stand out is that each apartment has been fitted out with a unique interior design finish. Each apartment has been thoughtfully finished to a high standard with bespoke design solutions in every apartment.

There is carpet flooring throughout all hallways and bedrooms with wood effect tiles in the kitchen / living / dining gives the apartments a high-end luxurious feel. Each apartment is provided with an office desk and chair for modern living styles. The attention to detail in Elmville allows residents the opportunity to unwind and settle down in their new home.

Every residence at Elmville is equipped with an intercom, generous storage space and air-source heat-pumps to ensure high energy efficiency and low running costs. There is secure underground parking and residents also benefit from ample bike storage facilities.

Harold's Cross is stylish, trendy, and steeped in history, the village is home to an eclectic mix of restaurants, pubs and things-to-do. The sense of community is as strong as ever and the park hosts an annual festival with live entertainment, arts and crafts and fun for all the family. Harold's Cross boasts some beautiful architecture, an exciting entertainment scene and it has more than its fair share of noteworthy spots serving up delicious coffee and fresh pastries every day.

The Dublin Bus nos. 9, 16, 49, 54A and 83 all include Harold's Cross on their routes and indeed, the endless spoils of neighbouring Rathmines and Ranelagh are within immediate reach by foot.

Parking is available at an additional charge.

Title: 1 Bedroom Apartment, Elmville, Harolds Cross Road, Harolds Cross, Dublin 6W
Description:
1 Bedroom Ground Floor Apartment

Elmville offers stunning 1-bedroom apartment; comfortable, very tastefully designed and flooded with natural light. The apartment is thoughtfully furnished and finished to a high standard with the notable treatment of bespoke interior design solutions, wholly unique to the unit.

The entrance hallway is generously sized with thick light grey carpeting to create an immediate sense of welcome. The interior here utilises a soft light grey and tan colour palette with warm lighting, suggestive of the overall comfort and security that the home offers. A large square gilded mirror hangs above a wide and shallow table in the hall, contemporary minimalist in design which fits the space perfectly.

The fully equipped kitchen/dining area features brick tiling splash backs and sleek modern workspaces with several high performance appliances. The integrated dishwasher, washer/dryer, oven and ceramic hob are from Beko, the microwave is Teka and the fridge/freezer is Electrolux - all highly efficient. Key in the design of the kitchen is its marriage of vintage and contemporary; it is aesthetically ‘homely’ and almost familiar while it celebrates and accommodates our more modern lifestyles.

The dining area enjoys the openness and flow from the kitchen while remaining its own intimate setting. The table is well sized and keeps with the soft grey theme with comfy seating such that the space brings all the right majesty to meal-time aided by the luxurious beige leather chairs which really compliment the space aided by the soft lighting of a featured lampshade directly above the table.

The dining area leads on to the main living space where a large stylish rug with hints of blue creates a generous and airy openness among the seating, which includes a matching soft yellow two-seater couch and armchair as well as a stylish grey single-seater offering lots of options for relaxing in the space. There is a dedicated work station to the side of the living area, private and secluded with a comfortable desk and chair, created with modern living in mind. Floor-to-ceiling sliding doors flood the room with natural light, leading out on to a large patio which runs the width of the room.

The bedroom is designed to champion downtime - with a sanctuary of solitude and rest. Thick carpeting and a laid-back colour palette ensure that the rooms maintains their own relaxed atmosphere, separate to whatever hustle and bustle might lie beyond the door.

The bedroom offers a very comfortable and low-standing bedframe, picking up the room’s subtle tones with an attractive wooden trim. This extends to the wardrobe, bedside locker, chest of drawers and an elegant dressing table to complete the suite. Floor-length curtains will guarantee darkness when required, but the window is thoughtfully positioned to make the most of the morning light. Featuring an ensuite bathroom with attractive wood-effect flooring and a large shower with marble wall-tiling.

The uniqueness of Elmville is that the keen eye of the interior designer is evident throughout and the main bathroom is no exception. The large bath/shower delightfully features the notorious chic subway wall tiles, a long-standing favourite in practical-meets-pleasing bathroom design.

The apartment is fitted with an intercom system for permission of access from within. The home is heated using an air-source pump and heat-recovery unit, a sensible and modern solution - highly efficient with low running costs.

Parking is available at an additional charge.
Facilities: Central Heating, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Parking, Washing Machine
DevelopmentTitle: Elmville , Harolds Cross Road, Harolds Cross, Dublin 6W

Title: U Clonsilla, Windmill Lodge, Dublin 15
Description:
U by Urbeo is proud to present U Clonsilla, a brand-new residential development located in Clonsilla, Dublin 15. This exciting new development offers a range of beautiful Studio, 1 and 2 bed apartments. All homes in U Clonsilla are "A" rated energy efficiency, meaning residents will enjoy comfort and warmth all year round. Ample storage is provided in all unit types and the interiors have been tastefully designed by Ventura Design.


- Parking Available 
- Dedicated management team on call
- Residential lounge
- Storage facility available


U Clonsilla is ideally located within short distance of Blanchardstown Shopping Centre. In this area, residents will find a handful of choices of grocery shopping stores, schools, creches, colleges, restaurants, and bars. MD Living is proud to introduce Kilcarbery Square, a brand-new development consisting of One, Two- and Three-Bedroom Homes. Kilcarbery Square overlooks Corkagh Park, which is one of Ireland's largest parks in which local residents are spoilt for choice as there is something for the whole family to enjoy. Jogging, golfing, or even playing baseball are all but a stone throw away from Kilcarbury Square as both Corkagh Park and Grange Castle Golf Club are a few minutes walk away.

The surroundings environs offer a range of amenities ranging from sporting pursuits such as GAA, golf and rugby, as well as the Clondalkin Leisure Centre and a wide range of cafes and restaurants. Local transport links include the excellent train service at both Clondalkin/Fonthill or Adamstown train stations and the LUAS Red Line at The Red Cow, each of which have superb park and ride facilities. Title: The Oslo , Sandyford Central , Sandyford, Dublin 18
Description:
For further information please visit www.theosloliving.ie

Welcome to The Oslo, where the essence of Hygge living awaits in our spacious apartments in the heart of Sandyford. These exquisite, well-lit, residences seamlessly blend the timeless allure of Scandinavian design with modern amenities, offering you the best of contemporary living.
Step into an apartment at The Oslo, and you'll discover an oasis of generous space, abundant natural light, and unparalleled comfort. Immense floor-to-ceiling windows invite the outdoors in, while meticulously crafted interiors create a tranquil atmosphere, serving as a stylish escape from the vibrant city life.

The Oslo is a testament to our commitment to nature's presence. Inspired by our idyllic location at the foot of the Dublin Mountains, we have designed a space that harmoniously integrates the urban environment with breathtaking vistas of the mountains and Dublin Bay. Residents can enjoy well designed amenities including the expansive Garden Lounge, a verdant sanctuary with a private garden, seamlessly linking through lush communal areas that connect to the LUAS transport system, shops, offices, and the bustling Sandyford Business District.

Every apartment at The Oslo has been thoughtfully designed with natural, comfortable living in mind. Our interiors showcase the finest in Scandinavian sustainable design, featuring natural fabrics and soothing colour palettes. Step out onto your spacious balcony, where you can enjoy a front-row seat to the ever-changing beauty of the natural world throughout the year.
Whether you choose a studio, one-bedroom, two-bedroom or three-bed apartment you'll find each one to be an instantly relaxing haven. Beautiful high-spec kitchens and ample storage space combine style with practicality seamlessly.

The Oslo is the perfect choice for those who relish the great outdoors, thanks to its prime location nestled between the mountains and the sea. You're just minutes away from hiking in the Dublin Mountains, biking in Ticknock, sea swimming in Monkstown, or leisurely strolls on Killiney Beach.
Excellent connectivity ensures that residents of The Oslo can effortlessly reach their desired destinations. Sustainable travel is made convenient with a multitude of walking and cycling tracks, coupled with the LUAS right at your doorstep. Additionally, easy access to the M50 ensures smooth journeys to more distant places.

The Oslo offers a host of features to enhance your living experience:

- Complimentary WiFi and TV Package
- Reception lobby 
- Co-working lounge
- Games room with pool table
- Garden lounge leading onto the landscaped terrace
- Chef's kitchen and lounge
- Gym* (*availability not guaranteed and subject to terms & conditions).

The Oslo is more than just a place to live; it's a lifestyle that embraces the principles of Hygge. Title: Archway Court Student Accommodation, Mountjoy St, Dublin 1
Description: STUDENT ONLY ACCOMMODATION. Archway Court is Student specific accommodation and is shared accommodation. The complex is made up of 12 Houses & 3 Apartments around a central courtyard with rooms to rent in each house. Archway is a gated development and tenants have pedestrian access via the pedestrian gate with a swipe fob. Currently we have limited availability for renting for the academic year & can be extended by mutual agreement. Licence terms are for a minimum of  6 months with 9 months or 12 month licence options also available. . Archway Court is independent living shared accommodation. This gated complex is within walking distance of the a range of 3rd level institutions/ colleges, including the new Grangegorman Educational Campus, Trinity College, The Kings Inn, DIT and Dublin Business School and the City Centre, O'Connell Street/ Henry Street, Dublins main shopping and entertainment district. Wifi service and bin collections are included in the rental price. The layout of the bedrooms varies from one room to the other. Public transport is easily accessible with a number of bus routes nearby and the Luas (Tram) runs along Mountjoy Street, right outside the gate. There are both single and shared rooms within the houses. Monthly rent prices vary depending on the room type. The Kitchens, Living Rooms and Bathrooms in the houses are shared by all Students.
Facilities: Internet, Laundry, Microwave, Washing Machine
