Title: St. Clare’s Park, Harold's Cross Road, Harold's Cross, Dublin 6
Description:
Stunning Development in the Heart of Harold's Cross, with Superb Onsite Amenities.

Visit www.stclarespark.ie to register your details.

* One, two and three-bedroom apartment available to rent *

St Clare's Park is a newly completed high-quality development of spacious apartments, ideally located in
the centre of bustling Harold's Cross overlooking Harold's Cross park. The architecturally striking,
beautifully designed development, which includes a large, landscaped courtyard.

The impressive development is not only excellently located but benefits from a wide range of apartment
layouts in the sensitively restored convent alongside the newly built residences. The new apartments are
very spacious, well-proportioned and elegantly finished with contemporary design and bespoke furniture
fit-out package. There are original features throughout the restored convent, with apartments full of
character and charm. There is a pet friendly block* and all apartments are wired for TV, cable and
broadband.

The development has state of the art on site resident's amenities, making St. Clare's Park a self
contained urban oasis catering to all its residents' needs. The resident's amenities are in the original
church which has been extensively refurbished making the amenity space unique compared to anything
else currently in the market.

St. Clare's Park residents will benefit from the following amenities:

- Concierge style services
- Gym
- Multimedia / Cinema Room
- Resident's Lounge area
- Coffee Dock
- Games Room
- Landscaped courtyard with BBQ area
- Car parking and bike storage facilities
- Children's Playground

These large apartments are excellently located, only 500 metres from the Canal, with the nearby vibrant
villages of Harold's Cross, Portobello and Rathmines a short stroll away; and easy accessibility to the
citycentre, Docklands, IFSC and beyond - the property is only 2km from St. Stephen's Green. Proximity to
Dublin 8 is also a major advantage. The area has excellent transport links with the 9, 16, 49, 54A and 83
Dublin Bus routes, all bringing you into city centre and the M50 is a short distance away. linking Harold's
Cross to other areas in Dublin and beyond.

Residents will be spoilt for choice with an abundance of parks, excellent cafes, restaurants, shops, salons
and boutiques in Harold's Cross as well as in the neighbouring Portobello, Rathmines and
Terenure.There is also a wealth of sports and leisure amenities from swimming facilities in the Swan
Centre to tennis in Rathgar and yoga in Harold's Cross, and the nearby canal for picturesque strolls.

*T&C 's apply*

Please note - the listed buildings at St Clares are BER exempt.

Older buildings may not be as energy efficient as new builds.

*** Register Your Interest Now at www.stclarespark.ie or email info@dubliv.ie ***

Title: Marietta Woods, Castle Park Road, Dalkey, Co. Dublin
Description:
Broadband & TV Package included

Marietta Woods is a brand new development designed for modern, elegant living.  

For more information please visit: www.mariettawoods.ie

The homes comprise a striking crescent-shaped block, set among beautiful mature woodland in Dalkey, a long established and highly sought-after residential address.  

The exterior presents a combination of bright brickwork and charcoal black highlights to accentuate its curves and symmetry, thus creating a collective grandeur in the overall aesthetic.  The structural nuances in the architecture protrude and recess to interact delightfully with the changing angles of the sun.  

Residents will also benefit from a private dedicated pavillion, which houses a gym and residents' lounge.  There is an outdoor children's play area and ample parking for 80 cars and 160 bicycles.  Manicured 'wild' areas punctuate the foot of the building, pulling the beauty of the wooded surroundings right to the door.  


The apartments in Marietta Woods are spacious and very thoughtfully designed and each one has been afforded individual consideration to achieve the perfect balance of practicality and style within the home.  

Marietta Woods is located in Dalkey, a coastal village, ten kilometres south of the city centre, which offers a unique mix of urban convenience and suburban amenity.  

Nestled among stunning mature woodland, Marietta Woods takes prominent position in Dalkey on Dublin's south side.  One of Ireland's best kept secrets, Dalkey is vibrant, exciting and above all, picturesque from end to end.  The town is culturally rich and steeped in history with a strong enduring sense of community.

The rent advertised on the individual property ads represent the starting rent for these property types.

Owen Reilly is delighted to present to the rental market, this stunning three bedroom apartment situated on the sixth floor at Opus, 6 Hanover Quay in the centre of Dublin's Docklands. Large companies in the area include Google, TikTok and Salesforce which ensures a strong rental market. Transport links are numerous with the Dart and Luas only five minutes away.

Title: Mount Argus Apartments, Mount Argus Road, Harold's Cross, Dublin 6W
Description:
The newest way to rent in Dublin
 
The Perfect Location
In Harold's Cross, a leafy, vibrant southside village 
Just a short stroll from ..
Rathmines
Grand Canal
Rathgar and Ranelagh, with fabled watering holes and eateries
Trendy Portobello and Camden St
Or a relaxing walk to ...
Dublin City Centre
Grand Canal Dock offices
Aviva Stadium 
Bord Gais Energy Theatre
A short spin in the car to...
Dublin Bay
St Vincent's Hospital
 
Private Resident Amenities  
Can't face driving through bumper-to-bumper traffic to watch the latest big-screen blockbuster in an expensive picture house? Well, Mount Argus has its very own modern cinema, which screens an array of top movies and big footie games. A self-contained world, the apartment complex also boasts a superb state-of-the-art gym - suitably refreshed after a weights or cardio session, you can then relax in the residents' lounge for more chilled-out downtime. 


The Apartments - One, Two and Three bedroom
Mount Argus offers a quality of life that other developments simply can't match. Nestling near verdant village parks, hipster eateries and the Grand Canal, the architecturally slick apartment complex includes a range of expertly designed and constructed one, two and three-bedroom apartments that cater for all the needs of today's busy individuals.

All of Mount Argus's spacious rooms are fitted with relaxing, fashionable furniture, and each light-filled apartment boasts private balconies or terraces, which allow for stunning views of local and urban landmarks. You can also while away the time in the landscaped resident's courtyard or chilled-out residents' area. Inside, the thermostatically-controlled central heating ensures life in Mount Argus is always warm and inviting for residents and their dogs and cats (the complex is pet-friendly). 

These spacious apartments are ideal for modern living.


Eco-friendly Mount Argus has substantial, secure bicycle storage space, and there is car parking in the basement.     
     
Kitchens/Dining areas
Mount Argus's purpose-designed kitchens are fitted with hi-spec accessories that are designed to make residents' lives that little bit easier. No detail is left untouched, as demonstrated by the user-friendly worktops, and expertly designed - and generous - storage spaces. As eye-catching are the top-of-the-range fridge freezers, dishwashers and combi ovens. Furthermore, the apartments have utility-storage rooms with washer-dryer machines, and there are supplementary storage room-home offices in the hallway.  
 
Living Rooms
Contemporary and comfortable, the well-proportioned living rooms are designed to blend in with the bespoke furniture that comes with the apartments. Elegantly designed, they are all wired for TV, cable, satellite and broadband services. Sit back and relax .    
 
Bedrooms
Mount Argus's spacious one, two and three-bedroom apartments are fitted with comfortable soft furnishings and elegant, purpose-designed furniture. Of course, generous fitted wardrobes are standard in all sleeping spaces, which include television, cable, satellite and broadband. 	
 
Bathrooms
The main bathrooms include attractive, modern shower-bath combi systems - naturally, our en-suites are all fitted out with invigorating showers. 
 
Service
To ensure everything runs smoothly in your new home in Mount Argus, the dedicated team at Hooke & MacDonald are on hand to assist in any management or maintenance queries. An expert onsite residents' manager will help with all your needs and queries. The array of onsite services includes a super-efficient dry-cleaning system - which allows you to pick up your clothes, at the push of a button, when you need them - and a secure, on-time parcel-management service. Peace of mind is guaranteed by our 24 hour-accessible resident's online app. 

 
Rapid Transport Links  
A true neighbourhood, Harold's Cross is served by multiple bus routes - the 9, 16, 49, 54A and 83 will speed you in to town, the 16 connects to Dublin Airport and a Nightlink service (49N) will get revelers back from that nightclub - but you don't have to rely on public transport, as the village is so central. An amble into St Stephen's Green will take around 30 mins and a Dublinbike (or your own bicycle) will get you there in around 10 . about the same it takes to drive to the M50. 

Leading Leisure 
Budding Federers and Serenas will love Rathgar Tennis Club, while the Leinster Cricket and Kenilworth Bowling clubs offer more relaxed recreation. The Swan Leisure complex's swimming pool is popular with beginners and expert front-crawlers, while Satya Yoga Club provides a calming alternative. Furthermore, the area brims with soccer and rugby clubs, while Bushy Park, Harold's Cross Park, Eamonn Ceannt Park and the Grand Canal are walkers' paradises.  


Superb shopping
In the heart of Rathmines is the bustling Swan Shopping Centre, which includes a large Dunnes Stores outlet, Omniplex Cinema (opposite the retro Stella cinema), bookshops, butchers and more. Even more local is Harolds Cross's handy Centra store, while nearby Kimmage has a superb SuperValu. Hipster-friendly Portobello and South Richmond St are famed for their ethnic food markets, while Grafton Street - just 20-25 minutes walk - brims with big-names stores. 
              
Bustling bars and eateries
An appetiser .
Peggy Kelly's and the Harold House are friendly "locals", Rathmines's lively watering holes include Roddy Bolands and Blackbird, and The Bleeding Horse is a cosmopolitan establishment across the canal. Craft on Harold's Cross Road and Clanbrassil St's Konkan Indian restaurant are just two of the acclaimed eateries. Then there's Five Points Café, Beckett & Bull . 

Excellent schools
Like other well-established Dublin neighbourhoods, Harold's Cross has plenty of school and childcare options (including crèches) for its residents. The lengthy list of prestigious local primary and secondary schools includes The High School; Alexandra College; Stratford College; St. Louis Primary and High Schools; St. Mary's College; Our Lady's School; and Terenure College. Of course, these are all within easy reach, so lengthy, stressful commutes aren't necessary.

2) The rent advertised on the individual property ads represent the starting rent for these property types. Rents will vary throughout the development depending on the specific property type. Not all the available properties and rents are listed here; please use those available at viewings. 

3) The overall BER Rating on this development is A Rated, an individual BER cert for your specific apartment is available on move in, upon request.

Title: The Locks, Charlemont Square, Dublin 2, Charlemont Street, Dublin 2
Description:
Elegant 1, 2 & 3 Bedroom Apartments and Penthouses To Let

Charlemont Square is a landmark new development offering luxurious apartments and penthouses in a prime Dublin 2 location—just a short walk from Ranelagh, Portobello, and St. Stephen's Green.

Developed by the acclaimed McGarrell Reilly Group, this vibrant city-centre scheme blends high-end living with urban convenience. At the heart of the development is a beautifully landscaped public plaza, home to cafés, restaurants, retail units, and a Tesco supermarket, placing every essential amenity at residents' fingertips.

Each apartment is meticulously designed with a focus on light, space, and contemporary comfort. A2-rated for energy efficiency, homes feature floor-to-ceiling windows, bespoke kitchens with quartz countertops and integrated Siemens appliances, and spacious utility rooms with built-in shelving, washing machine, and dryer.

Apartments also benefit from high ceilings, light grey wood flooring, and excellent built-in wardrobe storage throughout. Many units include a Winter Garden—an enclosed balcony space ideal for relaxation or enjoying the outdoors all year round. Bathrooms and ensuites are finished with premium Villeroy & Boch sanitary ware, rain showers, and heated towel rails.

Residents enjoy exceptional views of the city, mountains, and canal, all within a secure, beautifully crafted urban setting.


Tenant Amenities:

Central landscaped plaza with cafés, restaurants, and retail

Outdoor gym equipment and children's play area

Secure basement parking

Concierge and on-site management suite

Parcel collection service

Future shared car service

Krewe gastro bar

Tesco supermarket

Maser Art Studio

Dry cleaning service

Housekeeping service

Resident app for Android/iPhone

Sigmoid Golf - indoor golf simulators

Hair salon

Yoga Dublin - opening September

Jackie Tracey Interiors

McCauley's Pharmacy

Dedicated rooftop terrace with spectacular views over Dublin

Landscaped courtyards


Location
The Locks at Charlemont Square offers unrivalled connectivity and lifestyle in one of Dublin's most desirable city-centre locations. Residents are just minutes from Dublin's top retail and dining districts, including St. Stephen's Green and Harcourt Street, while the vibrant suburbs of Ranelagh and Rathmines are just a six-minute walk away.

The area is exceptionally well-served by public transport, with the Luas Green Line a three-minute stroll away and numerous Dublin Bus routes at the doorstep. GoCar and Dublin City Bikes are also conveniently located nearby.

For those who enjoy the outdoors, scenic walking routes include St. Stephen's Green, Iveagh Gardens, and the Grand Canal Walk, located just one minute from the development. The central plaza is also enhanced with outdoor fitness equipment, a children's playground, bike racks, and pristine landscaping—offering a peaceful escape in the heart of the city.

Title: Charlotte Apartments, Honeypark, Dun Laoghaire, Co. Dublin
Description:
Pet friendly*

Located opposite the 5 acre park at Honeypark, Charlotte Apartments overlook the on-site shopping facilities at Park Pointe which include Tesco Metro, Costa Coffee and Base Pizza to name just a few. Bus routes are located conveniently outside Honeypark making the DART and city center easily accessible. The Charlotte Residence Manager is located on site and a 24 hours a day online building service is also available. 

The Charlotte Building has recently been awarded a WiredScore Certified ratings under the residential certification by WiredScore, the internationally recognised real estate rating scheme for digital connectivity. The WiredScore rating reflects the buildings' excellent connectivity offering.  

The Charlotte's residence lounge has recently been updated along with childrens indoor play area.

LIVING ROOM, KITCHEN & DINING ROOM 
The living spaces in Charlotte are well designed to maximize space. Living rooms feature a contemporary and vibrant furniture package fitted out to an impressive standard. Elegant and modern kitchen designs have been created for Charlotte with painted shaker doors and sleek, slimline brushed aluminum door handles. Wired for TV, Cable, Satellite and telephone data.

Bathrooms 
Cool clean Sandringham taps, modern baths, sleek contemporary sanitary ware are all fitted as standard. Tiled in Blanco tile, with Goteborg Feature tile. A paneled, light walnut wood feature housing holds the mirror and incorporates vanity lighting.

BEDROOM 
The bedrooms are all large rooms with purpose designed bedroom furniture. Day and Night blinds provided throughout. There is ample storage space with Ivory Shadow wardrobes with Walnut trim. Wired for TV, Cable, Satellite and telephone data.

ADDITIONAL FEATURES
Storage Area - The large storage area houses the Heat Recovery Unit and the Hot Water System Hub. These two systems are relatively small and tidy, leaving the rest of the room free to use as storage. Heat Recovery System - Charlotte Apartments have a state of the art hot water and heating system which means residents will always have hot water and heat whenever required while resulting in less energy used and lower running cots. Hot Water/ Heating System - Hot water is heated centrally within the development from where it is available to all residents as required " on tap" . Due to this hot water is available constantly and the apartment resident only pays for what they use. Prepago Heating - The next generation Prepago Heating control system allows residents to control and monitor their heating remotely with the swipe of a finger on a smartphone. Residents can simply top up online using the Snugzone App. Pinergy - This next generation electrical control system allows residents to manage and monitor electricity usage remotely. There are no monthly electricity bills. Residents can simply top up online using the Pinergy Smart App.

Flooring - Entrance halls, en suites and bathrooms are floored with Goteborg porcelain tiles. Floors in living areas, bedrooms and utility/ storage rooms are finished with " Quick Step Click" wood flooring. Internal doors - Cherrywood flush front door with elegant walnut inlay border and cherrywood flush doors internally with high quality minimalist Senelli/ Linosa door handles.

Windows - Glazing to the apartments are A-Rated uPVC/ Aluminum windows with door access onto private balconies or terraces with most apartments. 

Balconies - Powder coated steel and glass balconies have maintenance free decking, many with exceptional views overlooking the 5 acre park at Honeypark, Marconi Park as well as the Charlotte central Gardens.

*T & C's apply

 ** Please note photos may not be specific to this apartment but all apartments are finished to similar standard **

ADDITONAL FEATURES
Storage Area – The large storage area houses the Heat Recovery Unit and the Hot Water System Hub. These two systems are relatively small and tidy, leaving the rest of the room free to use as storage.

Heat Recovery System – Charlotte Apartments have a state of the art hot water and heating system which means residents will always have hot water and heat whenever required while resulting in less energy used and lower running costs.

Hot Water/ Heating System – Hot water is heated centrally within the development from where it is available to all residents as required “on tap”. Due to this hot water is available constantly and the Charlotte apartment resident only pays for what they use.

Pinergy – This next generation electrical control system allows residents to manage and monitor electricity usage remotely. There are no monthly electricity bills. Residents can simply top up online using the Pinergy Smart App.

Flooring - Entrance halls, en suites and bathrooms are floored with Goteborg porcelain tiles. Floors in living areas, bedrooms and utility/ storage rooms are finished with “Quick Step Click” wood flooring.
Internal doors – Cherrywood flush front door with elegant walnut inlay border and cherrywood flush doors internally with high quality minimalist Senelli/ Linosa door handles.

Windows – Glazing to the apartments are A-Rated uPVC/ Aluminum windows with door access onto private balconies or terraces with most apartments.

Balconies – Powder coated steel and glass balconies have maintenance free decking, many with exceptional views overlooking the 5 acre park at Honeypark, Marconi Park as well as the Charlotte Central Gardens.

This beautifully renovated five bedroom home has been developed to the highest of standards with an exceptional finish throughout.

Off street parking is available by applying to DCC and the house is available for renting immediately.

Title: Cambridge House, 31 Sandycove Road, Sandycove, Co. Dublin
Description:
Sherry FitzGerald Lettings are delighted to present this magnificent period residence that perfectly blends Victorian grandeur with contemporary luxury. Situated behind secure electric gates on the prestigious Sandycove Road, this imposing home offers privacy, security, and sophisticated living just moments from the sea. Approached via a gravel driveway and granite steps, the property immediately impresses with its manicured topiary and classic cream-rendered façade. Inside, the home is defined by its grand proportions, featuring soaring ceilings, intricate cornicing, decorative archways, panelling and rich polished timber floors. 

The property boasts four distinct reception rooms, allowing ample space for both formal entertaining and relaxed family living. The drawing rooms are bathed in natural light through large sash windows and feature stunning marble fireplaces and period detailing. A standout feature is the stunning kitchen, equipped with both a wood burning stove and a classic Aga range, serving as the warm, inviting hub of the house. 
The residence includes four spacious bedrooms with sea views throughout, as well as three well-appointed bathrooms, all presented in immaculate condition, additional guest w.c.

Gardens & Grounds: To the rear lies a breathtaking landscaped garden. A true oasis of calm, it features a paved sun terrace, manicured lawns, and established beds filled with spectacular white hydrangeas and birch trees. A garden room provides excellent storage or potential for a home office, gym or children’s play room. 

Privacy & Security: The property is set behind electric gates with a high wall and is also equipped with a CCTV system and alarm, ensuring total privacy and security for residents. Cambridge House occupies an enviable position in one of Dublin’s most sought-after coastal suburbs. 

Residents can enjoy stunning sea views towards the famous "40 Foot" bathing place. The village of Sandycove and neighbouring Glasthule offer an array of boutique shops, gourmet restaurants, and cafes. The DART station is within walking distance, providing rapid access to Dublin City Centre.

Title: Apartment 21, Salthill, Monkstown, Co. Dublin
Description:
A beautifully finished three-bedroom, two-bathroom duplex apartment is now available in the exclusive Salthill development in Monkstown, one of South County Dublin’s most sought-after coastal locations. Extending to approximately 100 square metres, this own-door home is arranged over two levels and offers bright, dual-aspect interiors with exceptional views over Dublin Bay. The first floor is centred around a spacious open-plan kitchen, living and dining area, a superb contemporary space featuring solid oak flooring, high-quality fittings and integrated appliances. Large glazing opens directly onto a generous south-facing balcony that captures all-day sunshine, while a second balcony to the north provides an elevated vantage point across the landscaped grounds and out to the sea.

Upstairs, the main bedroom enjoys its own private balcony overlooking the bay, along with an en-suite finished to a luxurious standard. Two further bedrooms offer excellent comfort and storage, and the main bathroom includes a rain shower, bath and modern fittings. The property also benefits from attic storage, recessed lighting throughout and well-maintained interiors. Residents of this secure, gated development enjoy beautifully landscaped gardens and ample communal parking.

The location is one of the strongest features of this home. Salthill/Monkstown DART Station is just a two-minute walk away, providing rapid access to the city centre, Grand Canal Dock, Bray and the full coastal line. Monkstown Village is on the doorstep, known for its vibrant mix of restaurants, cafés, artisan food shops, boutique stores and friendly local services. Popular dining spots such as Avoca, Café du Journal, Bresson, That’s Amore and the Elephant & Castle are all within strolling distance, creating a lively village atmosphere. Dun Laoghaire, Blackrock and Dalkey are also close by, offering further options for restaurants, pier walks, shops, cinemas and cultural venues. The coastal setting provides easy access to swimming spots like Seapoint, the West Pier and Sandycove, as well as scenic shoreline walks stretching from Blackrock Park to the East Pier in Dun Laoghaire. The area is well connected for leisure activities, with nearby sailing clubs, tennis clubs, gyms, golf courses and the beautiful People’s Park market each weekend.

With its exceptional presentation, stunning sea views, private outdoor spaces and unrivalled proximity to Monkstown’s amenities and transport links, this is a rare opportunity to rent a premium property in a highly desirable coastal setting.

Title: 67 Merrion Grove, Blackrock, Co. Dublin
Description:
Stone Property are delighted to present this beautifully finished two-bedroom duplex apartment, ideally positioned beside the Radisson Hotel just off the Stillorgan Road.

Tucked away in a quiet, mature residential enclave, this exceptional home offers the perfect blend of privacy, style, and convenience. Bright and spacious throughout, it enjoys stunning views over immaculately landscaped gardens, creating a wonderful sense of calm and seclusion.

Accommodation

Arranged over two floors, this duplex is designed to maximise light, space, and flow. Both levels feature private balconies, ideal for morning coffee or evening relaxation while overlooking the tranquil gardens.

Upon entering, a welcoming entrance hall and staircase lead to a large living/dining room with high ceilings and direct access to the balcony — an elegant, airy space perfect for both entertaining and everyday living.

The kitchen/breakfast room on this level is bright and generously proportioned, combining practicality with a warm, inviting atmosphere.

On the lower level, the primary double bedroom opens to its own private balcony and offers ample wardrobe space. A second single bedroom provides flexibility for a guest room, home office, or nursery. The modern main bathroom is finished to a high standard, while a hot press and under-stair storage add everyday convenience. 


Location:

This superb location offers exceptional convenience and connectivity. A host of local shops and everyday amenities can be found in nearby Mount Merrion, while the vibrant villages of Booterstown, Blackrock, Stillorgan, and Donnybrook are all just a short drive away. For more extensive shopping and leisure options, Dundrum Town Centre is only minutes from your doorstep.

The area is exceptionally well served by public transport, with E1, E2, 47, and 7a bus routes, as well as the Aircoach providing quick and direct links to Dublin City Centre (approximately 7 km away, a 20-minute drive) and Dublin Airport.

Access to Booterstown:

An access path leads directly to the heart of Booterstown, where the DART station and Rock Road are just a 10-minute walk away — ensuring effortless commuting and easy access to the coast.

Summary of Features

Prime location beside the Radisson Hotel and Stillorgan Road

Bright and spacious duplex layout

Two private balconies with garden views

High ceilings and elegant living spaces

Modern kitchen and bathroom

Excellent storage throughout

Quiet, mature residential setting

Convenient access to Stillorgan, Blackrock, UCD, and city transport links

Transport links include the LUAS at Ranelagh village and bus services to the City centre along with good cycle lanes for easy city access.

The house is completed to BER A3 energy efficiency standard with full climate controlled underfloor heating, heat recovery system, constant fresh air ventilation and solar panel systems in place. 
With the triple glazing,  insulation and natural mechanical ventilation of this property, the house remains well heated throughout the year and in particular in winter, ensuring a cosy and healthy living environment.

The property in brief:

To the front, a paved and secure private parking bay with plantings which can accommodate 2 cars and doubles as a South facing enclosed terrace area. 

The open plan porcelain tiled ground floor consists of a contemporary hi-spec Siemens kitchen with stone counter tops and induction hob. The dining area has a feature marble table with seating for 6/8. The oak floored living room with a wood burning stove has 3 comfortable luxury leather sofas that look out into the manicured and decked rear garden with a unique water fountain feature. 
 
Just off the dining area there is also a uniquely designed study/ library room. A guest WC is also located on the ground floor.

The first floor has a light filled hallway and the accommodation consists of two very generous double bedrooms with plenty of built in wardrobe storage space. 

The  Master bedroom with a generous Emperor sized bed to the front of the property has a unique feature, that of a winter garden. The room also accommodates an en-suite with a walk-in shower cubicle. 

The guest bedroom is a spacious room with a Super king sized bed and additional space for a home office or sofa.


The first floor also hosts a designer main bathroom with a free-standing bath & walk-in shower. Additional under-stair storage is available here also.

The second floor has a private decked roof garden. Due to recent renovation; there is now additional accommodation for an office or 3rd (twin) bedroom and a monochromatic designer Guest WC/ Shower in leatherette porcelain finish.

The laundry/ Plant room is located on this floor too, fitted with all necessary appliances and ample space for natural drying if preferred.

A luxurious addition of a sauna room adds that something special to this beautiful modern home and with quick access to the outdoors, one could truly enjoy a Nordic experience.

All modern conveniences are catered for in this spectacular 'green' townhouse:

- The property is fully furnished 
- Solar powered/ Gas fired central heating
- A heat recovery system (so as no heat generated is wasted) 
- Solar powered water system (for constant hot water 24hrs a day) 
- Underfloor heating ensuring balanced comfort all year round
- Superior BER A3 energy efficiency rating
- Fully sealed home with controlled mechanical ventilation
- A fitted kitchen with quartz countertops and with all Siemens appliances
- TV/ Cable/ Internet services available
- CAT 6 throughout the property
- Off street secure parking for 2 vehicles on the paved front drive
- Private decked & paved rear garden with unique Water feature & planting
- Laundry room
- Sauna
- Private roof garden
- Alarm system
- Plenty of storage

The House will be deep cleaned with all windows washed prior to the 21st of November.
Viewings are available now by appointment. Please book by phone.

Title: Rathdown Villas, Dublin 6w, Terenure, Dublin 6W
Description: Sherry FitzGerald Lettings are delighted to present this exceptional, newly renovated, unfurnished home in Terenure to the Lettings Market. The property, originally the home of the Stringer family, is located in Rathdown Villas which consists of a double row of identical Stringer-built homes dating from the 1930s. It has been completely renovated inside and out, to the highest design standard under the direction of Lucy Jones Architects. It is 1,780 sq. ft. with four bedrooms 2 double and 2 single, 3 bathrooms and a naturally lit floored attic accessed by a remote control Stira. The house has an age–proofed, modern German Kitchen with separate Utility room and underfloor heating throughout, Dining Room with double doors leading onto a decked patio and a West-facing sunny garden with apple trees, Restful front Drawing room, downstairs Wet Room and a Home office/Playroom. There is a maintenance free front garden with off-street parking for two cars and an electric car charge point. The house retains all its original features and charm but has been renovated to encompass all the necessities for modern living. Located within walking distance of Bushy Park and Terenure Village which provides an abundance of Cafes, Restaurants, Shops, Leisure facilities and places of worship; R.C., CoI and Synagogue. Well served with Local Schools of all denominations including St. Joseph’s, Presentation Convent, Terenure College, Our Lady’s Girls School, Stratford College and the High School. Good public transport with easy Access to M50 and 25 minutes to Dublin Airport. Available to let from early  October 2025 , this exceptional home really must be viewed. Interested parties are advised to contact us to arrange a viewing!

Title: Sitric Road, Stoneybatter, Dublin 7
Description:
Lovely Artisan house on the best little street in Stoneybatter.

This house is in the centre of Sitric Road in Stoneybatter. One of the many things that make Sitric Road so cool is the beautiful old shop fronts, one of which is the bookshop and publishing house the Lilliput Press. Stroll down to the bottom of the street and you will find Lilliput Stores, which stocks the arguably best coffee in Dublin. This little shop won the Best shops in Ireland Irish Times award and it's right on the doorstep. Up the top of the street is Slice Restaurant, which is a great place to relax over a lazy Sunday brunch. Add to this the annual street party the Sitric Picnic and you have a pretty unique atmosphere on the road and a great community spirit. 

It's full of light and the sun catches the yard at the back for most of the day. It's cosy in winter especially when you get the open fire going, which warms the house from top to bottom. It was completely refurbished 10 years ago but most of the original features are still in the house, like the floor boards and doors. It has 2 good sized double bedrooms upstairs, a nice galley kitchen with loads of work-space, and plenty of space for parking out the front.

Stoneybatter has everything you need including great pubs and restaurants  Mulligan's for example is the excellent gastro pub just around the corner. 

The best thing about the area though is how close it is to town. 15 minutes walking will have you on Dame Street, or if you prefer to get in speedier there are loads of Dublin bikes stands around. Or if you want to shake off the city a bit, walk 10 minutes the opposite direction to the Phoenix Park. 

Its available to move into from the 7th of January 2026. Contact me, Sinead on above email address to arrange a viewing.
Facilities: Central Heating, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Parking, Washing Machine

Title: Bow Bridge Place, Kilmainham, Dublin 8, Kilmainham, Dublin 8
Description:
A bright, west-facing 2-bed ground floor apartment in turnkey condition, set within a secure and secluded parkland development just minutes from St James’s Hospital, St Patrick’s University Hospital, Heuston Station and the city centre.

The apartment benefits from beautifully landscaped communal gardens and is bordered by the River Camac.

Inside, the property comprises an entrance hall with storage closet, a spacious living room with floor-to-ceiling sliding doors opening onto a private patio area and communal gardens, and a modern fully equipped kitchen with generous dining space. There is one double bedroom with fitted wardrobes, and a second bedroom currently set up with two single beds (twin room), which can also be converted into a home office or double bedroom if preferred.

The bathroom was newly renovated in late 2025, finished to a high standard with modern tiling, updated fittings and an electric shower.

Tastefully furnished throughout and presented to a very high standard.

The location is excellent: a short walk to Heuston South Quarter with shops, cafés, gym, crèche and pharmacy. The Red Line Luas is only minutes away, and IMMA, the Memorial Gardens and Phoenix Park provide superb outdoor leisure options.

Available from 1st January for a minimum 12-month lease, with the option to extend long-term.

Viewing highly recommended.

Title: 8 Larkfield View, Dublin 18, Leopardstown, Co. Dublin
Description:
Turley Property Advisors are delighted to present to market this fine three-bedroom semi-detached home to the market to let. Built in 2017 this stunning A-Rated home has been upgraded by the current owners to include a lovely bespoke entertainment cabinet in the living room, stylish light fittings, and an extended garden patio. Due to the property’s location beside the playground, it has the benefit of a larger than standard garden for the development which has been used to place a useful garden shed. 
The house comes with the advantage of two off street parking spaces and an electric car charging point and additional features include a Ring alarm system, video doorbell, and outdoor security cameras that can be managed by the tenant via a Ring account. 

Upon entering the property, one is welcomed by a generous hall with staircase rising to the first floor and a smart guest w.c. To the left a spacious dual aspect living area has a lovely bespoke entertainment unit, and French doors opening to the garden. To the right of the hallway an open plan kitchen dinner again with dual aspect views and built-in kitchen by Nolan kitchens. Off the kitchen there is a useful utility/storeroom that opens to the rear garden. 
Rising to the first floor a generous landing with hot press leads to a lovely main bedroom suite with triple aspect views and built-in wardrobes. A fine ensuite with large shower suite lies off the bedroom. Two further spacious bedrooms also have built in wardrobes, and a lovely well-appointed family bathroom has the advantage of both bath and separate shower. 

Outside to the rear the garden is laid out in lawn and concrete paving with a large sun terrace and raised specimen planted beds. A useful wooden storage shed is set to the side of the garden. There is both external tap and external socket provided. A pedestrian side gate leads to the two off street parking spaces which lie to the side of the house. 
Clay Farm is positioned just off the Ballyogan Road and is convenient to a host of shopping outlets and eateries. The Luas stop at Leopardstown Valley is a leisurely three-minute stroll along with the Glencairn bus stop with the 47-bus service and allow for convenient access to the city centre, Sandyford Business Park and the Beacon Hospital, and the M50 and N11 (QBC) allow for travel further afield. 
Within the development there is the new greenway to Stepaside village along with lovely sylvan walks and playgrounds. 

Viewing is highly recommended.
Facilities: Alarm, Central Heating, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Parking, Washing Machine

Title: Seafield Lodge, Stillorgan Road, Donnybrook, Dublin 4
Description:
Hunters Estate Agent are delighted to introduce Seafield Lodge, Stillorgan Road to the market. Originally constructed in 1966 this charming, detached residence was completely refurbished throughout in 2003. Boasting approx. 3,230 sq. ft / 300 sq. m and standing on circa 0.25 acre the property is quietly set back from the road and is secured by walls and vehicular gates to the front.  

Seafield Lodge enjoys very spacious, and light filled living accommodation throughout which comprises briefly of entrance porch, entrance hallway, living room, family room and kitchen / breakfast room. Also, at this level there is an extra space which consists of a reception, bedroom, small kitchen and bathroom. At first floor level there are six bedrooms (one ensuite), utility room, shower room and family bathroom.   

Seafield Lodge occupies a most impressive secure and private site circa 0.25 acre, walled on all sides and is bordered by a mature hedging, trees and shrubbery. The front of the property is approached by double gates leading to secure off-street parking for several cars. The front and side gardens which are predominantly laid in lawn have been meticulously maintained. To the rear of the property there is a spacious paved patio area with retractable awning providing shelter from both the sun and rain. 

Seafield Lodge is superbly positioned and enjoys one of Dublin 4's most convenient locations being within easy reach of an extensive selection of amenities. Some of these amenities include UCD Belfield, St. Vincent's Private & Public Hospitals, Elm Park Golf Club and many of Dublin's premier schools such as St. Michaels, the Teresians, Muckross Park, Blackrock College, Mount Anville Secondary school, Colaiste Eoin & Colaiste Isogain and St. Andrew's College. The property also benefits from being within easy reach of the excellent shopping facilities such as Merrion Shopping Centre, Stillorgan Shopping Centre, Blackrock Shopping Centre and Dundrum Shopping Centre. The property is very well serviced by Dublin Bus routes 46a, 145, 155 which all run frequently.  


Viewing is essential and highly recommended.  
 
-	Superb 7-bedroom detached residence on circa 0.25 acre 
-	Built 1966 
-	Oil Fired Central Heating 
-	Security Gates 

-	Wonderful location within easy reach of city centre 
-	External insulation added 4 years ago 
-	Approx. 3,230 sq. ft / 300 sq. m

Title: Coolvalley, Abingdon Park, Shanganagh Road, Loughlinstown, Co. Dublin
Description:
-----------------------3 bedroom 2 bathroom Detached House To Let------------------------------------
-------------------------------------Short-term Let Only-------------------------------
--------------------------------6-month Only----------------------------------------------------

Approached via electric entrance gates, which open to reveal the graciously landscaped gardens which are truly something special to behold. Boasting a highly desirable south west facing orientation, with sweeping lawns, the periphery is bordered by mature hedging and trees, offering utter privacy and seclusion. To one side, a smaller lawn offers the perfect space for a grass tennis court. Designed in 1939 by renowned horticulturalist Humphrey Watson who was the first owner, the gardens contain a collection of specimen trees including Edwardzia, Myrtle, Cuban Laurel, Irish Oak, Weeping Willow, Laburnum, Magnolia, Stellata, Forsythia, Cordelina Australis and varieties of Cypress, Fir and Cedar. There is a patio area to the front of the property, an ideal space for al fresco dining in the Summer months and there's ample space for garden parties. Two garages, one double and one single as well as a detached studio measuring approx. 6m x 4.20, offer further versatile space which could be put to a multitude of uses including a home office, hobby room, home gym, yoga or art studio.
The location is excellent, just 15 minutes' walk from the vibrant village of Shankill offering a selection of local shops and supermarkets, including the Lidl and Tesco Express, alongside cafes and eateries including Bradys gastro pub. There is also a selection of highly regarded primary and secondary schools in the vicinity including St. Anne's National School, Rathmichael Parish School and Scoil Mhuire, Woodbrook College, St. Gerard's, John Scottus and there's easy access to a host of other secondary schools via the Dart. The beach at Shankill is within walking distance and nearby Shanganagh Park offers many walks, pleasure, recreational and sporting facilities. The DART is within 10 minutes' walk of the property and a number of bus routes pass through the village, including the aircoach to Dublin airport. The N11, M50 and the LUAS are all within minutes of the property offering seamless access to the city centre.

Title: Shore Club, Beach Road, Dublin 4
Description:
Owen Reilly is delighted to present this stunning, brand new two-bedroom, two-bathroom apartment located on the third floor of the prestigious Shore Club development in Sandymount, Dublin 4. Designed to combine city living with coastal tranquillity, Shore Club offers residents the best of both worlds — just moments from Sandymount Strand and within easy reach of Dublin’s vibrant city centre.

This beautifully finished apartment features a bright and spacious open-plan living and dining area, complemented by floor-to-ceiling glazing that fills the space with natural light. The modern kitchen is fully fitted with premium integrated appliances, sleek cabinetry, and ample storage, ideal for contemporary living. Both bedrooms are generous doubles with built-in wardrobes, while the main bedroom includes an en-suite bathroom. The main bathroom is luxuriously appointed with high-quality porcelain tiling and elegant sanitaryware. Oak laminate flooring runs throughout the living areas and bedrooms, adding warmth and style to the interior.

The apartment benefits from access to an impressive range of resident amenities, including a fully equipped gym, co-working space, cinema room, and landscaped courtyard with outdoor seating and recreational areas. A concierge service and 24-hour CCTV provide convenience and peace of mind, while residents also enjoy access to a car club and extensive bicycle parking.

Built to the highest modern standards, Shore Club is WiredScore Platinum certified, offering ultra-fast broadband connectivity, and is highly energy-efficient with an A-rated BER and an exhaust air to water heat pump system.

More about this location...

Nestled in the heart of Dublin 4, Shore Club enjoys a prime coastal setting in Sandymount — one of Dublin’s most desirable and picturesque neighbourhoods. The development sits just moments from Sandymount Strand, offering residents the rare opportunity to enjoy seaside walks and fresh sea air while remaining within easy reach of the city centre.

The surrounding area is renowned for its relaxed village atmosphere, with Sandymount Village offering an excellent selection of cafés, restaurants, and boutique shops. Nearby Grand Canal Dock and Ringsend provide an energetic urban contrast, home to tech giants such as Google, Meta, and TikTok, along with a host of trendy eateries and waterside amenities.

Transport links are exceptional. The Sydney Parade DART station and multiple Dublin Bus routes are within walking distance, ensuring seamless access to the city centre, the IFSC, and beyond. Dublin Airport is easily reached via the Port Tunnel, while cyclists benefit from nearby coastal and canal cycle paths.

Outdoor enthusiasts will appreciate the abundance of green and blue spaces nearby — from Sean Moore Park and Sandymount Strand to Herbert Park and Poolbeg Lighthouse. Whether it’s a morning jog along the coast, a coffee by the water, or a short commute into town, Shore Club’s location perfectly balances lifestyle, leisure, and connectivity.

Features

Exceptional brand new 2-bedroom, 2-bathroom apartment on the third floor.

Located in the prestigious Shore Club development, Sandymount, Dublin 4.

Prime coastal location – moments from Sandymount Strand and close to Dublin city centre.

Contemporary open-plan living space with premium finishes throughout.

Fully fitted modern kitchen with integrated appliances.

Brand new furniture throughout-apartment has never been lived in.
Two spacious double bedrooms with built-in wardrobes.

Two stylish bathrooms finished with porcelain tiles.

Oak laminate flooring in living areas and bedrooms.

WiredScore Platinum connectivity with dedicated 4 Gb fibre broadband.

Energy-efficient heating and hot water via exhaust air heat pump.

Private balcony offering excellent natural light.

Resident amenities include:

Fully equipped gym and wellness studio.

Co-working space and residents’ lounge.

Private cinema room.

Landscaped courtyard with seating areas, outdoor chess and ping pong table.

Concierge service and 24-hour CCTV security.

Car club with hybrid SUVs for resident use.

A2 BER Rating.

Excellent transport links via nearby DART, bus routes, and cycle paths.

Short walk to Sandymount Village, Ringsend, Grand Canal Dock, and city centre.

Title: 12 Royal Terrace West, Dun Laoghaire, Co. Dublin
Description:
Set along one of Dun Laoghaire’s most admired Victorian squares, No. 12 enjoys a privileged position with direct views across the beautifully maintained central gardens. The location offers a rare blend of peaceful residential surroundings while being only a short walk from the seafront, the DART, boutique shops, cafés, schools and coastal leisure amenities.

Behind the distinguished bay-fronted façade lies a bright and refined home that has been thoughtfully modernised while maintaining an extensive collection of original features, including ornate ceiling work, sash windows, window shutters, period fireplaces, solid wood floors and high ceilings throughout.

Accommodation

The ground floor comprises a welcoming lobby opening into a superb open-plan kitchen, dining and living space extending from the front to the rear of the house. This sociable space includes a feature fireplace, double doors to the garden, a separate utility room and a luxurious bathroom complete with Jacuzzi bath, infrared sauna and walk-in shower. Clever built-in storage and concealed wiring for sound enhance usability.

A bedroom with garden access and a guest WC sit on the return level. The hall floor features the formal entrance and two magnificent interconnecting reception rooms, both rich in period detailing and ideal for entertaining or quiet enjoyment, complemented by working shutters and elegant ceiling features.
On the upper return there is another bedroom and a modern shower room, while the top floor accommodates two generous double bedrooms. The principal bedroom spans the full width of the house, enjoys wonderful, elevated views extending towards Killiney Hill, and features extensive fitted storage and a striking period fireplace.

Location

This highly sought-after setting places a wealth of conveniences within effortless reach. Dun Laoghaire’s regenerated waterfront, its piers, sailing clubs and coastal bathing spots provide a superb outdoor lifestyle, while Glasthule and Monkstown villages offer artisan food shops, restaurants and relaxed neighbourhood cafés. Excellent transport links include the DART, Aircoach and numerous bus routes. Renowned schools, parks, tennis clubs, gyms and scenic coastal walking routes stretching towards Sandycove and Dalkey are all close by.

Gardens

The front garden is neatly presented with mature planting, while the impressive west-facing rear garden is accessed from both the ground floor and return. It offers a series of outdoor spaces including patio seating areas, lawn, fruit trees and leafy canopies. Alongside gated pedestrian access to a private laneway.

Key Features

•	Prestigious period home overlooking Royal Terrace Gardens
•	Four double bedrooms including full-width principal suite
•	Open-plan kitchen / dining / living space with garden access
•	Elegant interconnecting reception rooms with original features
•	Luxurious bathroom with Jacuzzi bath, walk-in shower and infrared sauna
•	West-facing Garden and rear laneway access
•	Short walk to DART, seafront, cafés, shops and schools

Title: Llandaff Terrace, Merrion Road, Merrion, Dublin 4
Description:
We are delighted to bringLlandaff Terrace, one of eight elegant double fronted town houses, which have been beautifully and sympathetically restored to the market for rent. These unique homes boast many features including high ceilings. The town houses are set back from the Merrion Road bordered by a railing and mature planting which offers privacy. Each house has the benefit of two car parking spaces. 

Located on Merrion Road in the heart of Dublin’s prestigious Dublin 4, Llandaff terrace has a host of amenities within easy reach. The villages of Blackrock, Sandymount and Ballsbridge are located nearby each with a bustling village atmosphere and an array of shops, restaurants, cafes and pubs making it an attractive place to visit. Close by you will also find the Aviva Stadium and the RDS. The immediate area is also home to Wanderers Rugby Club, Elmpark Golf and Sports Club, Donnybrook Lawn Tennis Club and Sandymount Strand. Many of Dublin’s top schools are also located close by including St. Andrews, Blackrock College,Willow Park, St. Conleth’s, St. Michaels, Sion Hill, Teresian School and Booterstown National School. There are several Universities, third level colleges and hospitals in the immediate vicinity including St. Vincent’s University and Public Hospital, Blackrock Clinic, University College Dublin, Trinity College Dublin and Royal College of Surgeons all within easy reach. Quality shopping facilities are located nearby in Blackrock, Frascati and Merrion Shopping Centres. Situated on the Merrion Road, close to the DART and N11, LLandaff Terrace’s location in Dublin 4 is one of its major attractions. Both the Merrion Road and N11 dual carriageway offer direct access to and from the city centre. The N11 also features a Quality Bus Corridor (QBC) that provides public transport links to the City, North, South and other surrounding areas. Also on your doorstep is the Aircoach which takes passengers to Dublin Airport via the Port Tunnel.

Accommodation
The accommodation comprises of large entrance hall, sitting room, separate dining room, kitchen, access to city garden, guest wc, two large double bedrooms, family bathroom with separate standalone shower. The property benefits from two designated car parking spaces.

Special Features
Double fronted period house with low maintenance west facing city rear garden. Cast iron gutters and down pipes. Double glazed windows throughout. Fully fitted kitchen with integrated electrical appliances fridge freezer, electric oven and hob, dishwasher, and extractor hood and fan. Fitted wardrobes. All bathrooms are fitted with high quality white sanitary ware throughout. Electrical Smoke heat and carbon monoxide detectors fitted. Broadband, TV, Phone & Intruder alarm. Heating is Gas fired central heating.
Rear City Garden Rear city gardens are landscaped including hard paving. Gardens include an array of specimen plants and shrubs. 

Directions
Travelling from Ballsbridge south bound, continue along Merrion Road, pass the junction at Merrion Gates. Turn right into Llandaff Terrace at Elmpark Green. Take immediate left. Llandaff Terrace is located on your right hand side overlooking Merrion Road.

Viewing comes highly recommended and all enquiries are by EMAIL only.

Owen Reilly is delighted to present this double fronted Georgian  residence Circa. 1840 and situated in the heart of the city centre, just minutes from Trinity College, Grafton Street, St. Stephens Green and the Docklands. This two storey over basement home offers spacious, well appointed accommodation offers dual aspect rooms with bright and spacious central staircase rising from garden level to first floor with original period features on three levels. The east facing garden with sunny patio is particularly attractive and private on a generous plot thanks to the double fronted nature of the property. In 2011 the house was comprehensively renovated/restored including new heating system and new energy efficient boiler, re-plastering of interior walls, new kitchen, new stone floor at garden level, new timber floors at entrance level, all decorative mouldings made good , opening up of chimney breasts and installation of wood burning stoves, provision of alarm system, full garden landscaping, new timber double glazed windows at garden level, new light fittings, new bathrooms including new stone floors. Given this the house is in excellent condition. The interior comprises entrance hall, living room, kitchen/dining room, three/four double bedrooms or second living room and two bathrooms. Ample on street permit parking to front.

More about the location...

This is a central location in one of Dublin's most vibrant neighbourhoods with a host of amenities close by including the Convention Centre, 3 Arena, Trinity College, Grand Canal Dock, Bord Gais Theatre, Aviva Stadium, IFSC, The National Gallery of Ireland and Science Gallery to name a few. Public Transport options are numerous: one minute to Dublin Bike Station, two minutes to Tara Street Dart Station and three minutes walk to Luas Green and Red lines.
Facilities: Dishwasher, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Microwave, Washing Machine

Title: 1 Seabury Meadows, Malahide, Malahide, Co. Dublin
Description:
Conerney Estate Agents are proud to present to market this fantastic 5 bedroom 3 bathroom house with garden situated in the sought after Seabury Meadows in Malahide, Co. Dublin. The property is end of estate offering privacy, security and private parking for 3 cars in the driveway (additional street parking free of charge). This property is in pristine condition throughout and fitted with high quality fixtures and fittings and it comes to market to a very high standard. The house is located at the end of the estate with a beautiful view overlooking the field & countryside area. In the kitchen you have a large electric hob with oven, 2 large American style fridge/ freezers, Dishwasher, Washing Machine, Clothes Dryer and lots of storage space. The open plan dining room & living room area is fitted with hardwood flooring, wooden table & chairs and a real fireplace with mantlepiece. The house is equipped with a back conservatory area, offering an amazingly comforting space t relax, which has a sliding door leading to the garden & patio with small shed. The house has a side entrance which is useful for storing bicycles, motorbike etc. 
The property has electric central heating and it's wired for high speed internet. Downstairs there is one very large double bedroom with built in wardrobes and double doors leading outside to the front of the house. The smaller 2nd double bedroom with built in wardrobes is also downstairs. Upstairs there are three large double bedrooms all fitted with built in wardrobes, one bedroom being an en-suite with shower. The main bathroom fully tiled, contemporary finish bitted with bath & shower. All in all, this is an incredible spacious and charming house presented in excellent walk-in condition throughout and set in a quiet and mature location, yet close to shopping centres, beside Seabury Park,  beside all major Dublin Bus transport link, The Dart Station, beside the M1 motorway and close to schools, shops and pharmacies. Please apply online, leave your name, phone number and email address and we will get back to you to arrange a suitable viewing time. VIEWING HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!

Title: 11 Obelisk Court, Saint Augustine'S Park, Blackrock, Co. Dublin
Description:
**Unfurnished House** Joseph Estates is delighted to present this wonderful modern home in Blackrock. The property is a well-proportioned (c. 130 sqm), beautifully presented 3-bedroom terraced house nestled in a quiet cul-de-sac at the rear of St. Augustine's Park which is situated just off Stillorgan Park Road. This is an excellent opportunity to rent a lovely home, suitable for either city centre commuting or for those looking for a residence close to Blackrock, Dun Laoghaire and Stillorgan.  St. Augustine's Park is a private residential neighbourhood with everything on its doorstep. Blackrock and Stillorgan villages are within easy walking distance as are several bus routes with the QBC. Blackrock DART station is also only approximately 10 minutes by foot.

Externally the house has a traditional brick finish to the front, giving a sense of quality and permanence to this wonderful home. The interiors provide an elegant living environment which flows beautifully on a practical level. The house has traditional features such as an elegant stone fireplace and tall ceilings with decorative cornice. This house is fitted to a high standard throughout with a bright and spacious fully fitted kitchen with all mod cons and beautiful granite counter tops . Both the main bathroom and the en-suite feature high quality sanitary ware accented with chrome taps and heated towel rails for everyday comfort. The property boasts wooden floors in the hallway and also on the ground floor is a warm and comfortable living room with an elegant stone fireplace with gas fire, and a sun drenched extension to the rear. There is also a small WC on this level. The first floor consists of two double bedrooms, one single bedroom and the main bathroom. The master bedroom is bright and airy and has fitted wardrobes providing ample storage space. The master also has a fully tiled en-suite with shower. The main bathroom is fully tiled and has a bath with shower mixer. The single bedroom has a fitted wardrobe for extra storage.  The attic has been tastefully converted to allow for a study / home office space and contains velux windows and fitted wardrobes for storage with the eves allowing for even further storage.

Garden and External area: The beautiful rear garden offers residents a private, secluded open space which is low maintenance, with a well-appointed shed offering ample storage space. To the front of the property there is private parking for 2 cars and an electric charge point for those with electric cars. The house has a BER C rating.

Location and Local Transport:
St Augustine's Park offers an excellent south Dublin location nestled amongst some of the city's most popular residential areas, in very close proximity to Blackrock, Dun Laoghaire, Dalkey, Killiney, Foxrock. The property is located 1.9km from Blackrock village, 1.5km from Stillorgan Village, 5.2km from Dun Laoghaire Harbour and has easy access of the N11 with QBC, the M50, the DART in Blackrock. The Luas in Stillorgan allows for a short 20 minute commute to both Dublin City Centre and Dundrum Town Centre.  The local area affords a variety of amenities including shops, boutiques, restaurants & bars, as well as a host of commercial services.  There are several large supermarkets within close proximity including Tesco, SuperValu, Lidl and Avoca outlets. The locality also boasts some excellent schools, both primary and secondary, including All Saints National School, Carysfort National School, Blackrock College, Willow Park, St Andrews College, Blackrock College and  Coláiste Eoin & Íosagáin. For lovers of the great outdoors, the sea is within easy reach, there are a number of local parks and there are large communal green areas within the development itself, which are perfect for recreational use and short walks. 

Available from the 18th of December 2025 , viewing by appointment only.
Facilities: Alarm, Cable Television, Central Heating, Dishwasher, Dryer, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Internet, Microwave, Parking, Washing Machine

Title: Shrewsbury, Dublin 4, Ballsbridge, Dublin 4
Description:
Set within a secure, gated community just off Merrion Road and only a short stroll from Ballsbridge, this exceptional bungalow offers 4 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, combining modern design with outstanding convenience. 

Approached through secure gates into a secluded courtyard, the accommodation is well laid out, featuring a bright and spacious open-plan kitchen, dining, and living area at its heart. Double patio doors extend the living space outdoors to a stylish patio. The four double bedrooms all include built-in wardrobes. Two of the bedrooms feature en-suite bathrooms and direct access to the outdoor spaces. A main bathroom completes the accommodation. The property further benefits from a self-contained unit in the back garden, complete with a kitchenette and en-suite, perfect as a home studio, office, or for hosting guests. 

Outside, the property offers paved patio areas to both the front and rear, including a dining space and a private walled courtyard – perfect for entertaining or everyday use. 

Both Ballsbridge and Sandymount villages are moments away, offering an enviable array of restaurants, artisan cafés, boutiques, and speciality food stores. The city centre, Grand Canal Dock, and Merrion Square are all within easy reach, while the RDS, the Aviva Stadium, the Bord Gáis Theatre, and the Intercontinental Hotel add to the world-class amenities nearby, in addition to the proximity to several of Dublin’s most highly regarded schools. 

This stylish home offers privacy, comfort, and convenience in one of Dublin’s most prestigious residential locations. 

Accommodation: 
• Kitchen / Living Area: Open-plan design with modern fitted kitchen, integrated appliances, tiled floor and patio access. 
• Bedroom 1: Double room with en-suite bathroom, fitted wardrobes, and access to rear garden. 
• Bedroom 2: Double room with en-suite shower room and access to patio. 
• Bedroom 3: Double room with fitted wardrobes. 
• Bedroom 4: Double room with fitted wardrobes. 
• Main Bathroom: Stylish tiled finish with walk-in shower and heated towel rail. 

Please email your enquiry with full details. Due to the volume of interest, replies to all emails may not be possible.
Facilities: Alarm, Central Heating, Garden / Patio / Balcony, Parking, Pets Allowed

Cromlech Fields is a highly regarded and well established location, offering residents easy access to a wide array of amenities. Nearby, the villages of Ballybrack and Shankill offer a variety of cafés, convenience stores, and local businesses providing everything you need within easy reach.

The bathroom is designed with functionality in mind, featuring heated towel rails, a rainfall shower, and a sleek vanity unit for a comfortable and efficient start to the day. Each bedroom is thoughtfully arranged, offering a tranquil space for rest and relaxation.

The house benefits from full insulation, ensuring a warm and energy-efficient environment throughout the year. Outside, the property boasts a well-kept garden with a patio, ideal for outdoor relaxation or dining amidst nature. The charm of the house is further accentuated by the elegant oak flooring that flows seamlessly throughout.

For entertainment and connectivity, the house is equipped with a Smart TV and Virgin Media TV and Internet services. Added conveniences include parking facilities and an alarm system, providing security and ease for residents.

With its recent renovations, full insulation, and thoughtful features, this house stands as a perfect blend of modern living and homely comfort.

The Locks is Dublin 2's most exciting and prestigious, new development superbly located in Charlemont Square, a new urban mixed use development for Dublin on Charlemont Street, between the Grand Canal and Harcourt Street. The development perfectly merges some of Dublin's coolest living addresses; Ranelagh, Rathmines and Portobello, alongside the city's leading social districts. 

The development offers all the benefits and convenience of City Centre living while also offering superb Mountain, Canal and City views.

Apartments are set around a stunning public plaza which hosts an array of amenities such as café's, retail space, restaurants and a Supermarket. There is a high spec kitchen located off the lounge with ceiling to floor storage and Siemens integrated appliances to include dishwasher, oven, microwave and full size fridge/freezer. There is the further benefit of a large utility area off the kitchen with excellent built in storage and a separate washing machine and dryer.

All bathrooms are complete with Vilroy Boch fittings with Rain Showers and large double size shower cubicles/bath. There is wood flooring throughout the apartment and attractive furnishings. 

This property is A2 rated and would make for a truly comfortable and convenient home in this prime location within walking distance of every imaginable convenience.

The Charlemont area has an abundance of public transport facilities which includes the Luas, only a 3-minute walk away, as well as several bus routes right outside your doorstep.

Title: Apartment 17, Block 3
Description:
One Springfield Park is an Exclusive collection of just 20 luxury A rated apartments located in Foxrock, Dublin 18. This two-bed property is finished to the highest of standards and features a luxury specification, top of the range kitchen and fixtures and fittings throughout. The apartment is Dual aspect and enjoys spectacular views of both Dublin Bay and Dublin Mountains. This apartment also includes a secure external storage unit, perfect for storage of bikes, golf clubs and other non-day to day household items.

The layout of the apartment is designed to offer comfortable living with generous storage provided. Occupants will enjoy an abundance of space, especially in in the kitchen living area which leads out to a private balcony.

One Springfield Park offers residents a secure and tranquil environment, with excellent transport options and a wide variety of amenities in close proximity. Foxrock is a popular leafy suburb nestled between Dublin Bay and the foothills of the Dublin Mountains. Centred on a small village, it is well-served with shops, restaurants and cafes, along with an excellent choice of schools.

A particular feature to Foxrock is the close proximity to Cabinteely Park which spans 45 hectares and includes excellent walks and a children's playground. There are numerous primary and secondary schools serving the area, such as St Brigid's Girls National School, St Brigid's Boys National School, Cabinteely Community School, Clonkeen College and Loreto Convent.

One Springfield lies just off the N11, only 12 kilometres from Dublin city centre. It is also accessible from Dun Laoghaire and the M50, via junction 15 Carrickmines. A number of bus routes operated by Dublin Bus serve Foxrock such as the 63, 84, 84a and 84x. The Luas Green Line passes close to Foxrock village with a stop at Carrickmines (about 20 minutes' walk from the development), with a journey time of less than 30 minutes to Dublin city centre.

Viewing is highly recommended!
Facilities: Central Heating, Parking

Townhouse, Wellington Road, Ballsbridge, Dublin 4

A masterclass in Victorian elegance and modern refinement, 25 Wellington Road is an exceptional five-bedroom, five-bathroom townhouse offering over 3,900 sq.ft of meticulously restored and extended accommodation in one of Dublin’s most prestigious addresses.
Beyond its handsome granite façade and electric gates lies a home of extraordinary quality — reimagined with exacting craftsmanship to combine period grandeur with contemporary luxury.
The formal reception rooms — with marble fireplaces, decorative cornicing, and soaring ceilings — flow gracefully to a bespoke kitchen and breakfast room, bathed in natural light and opening onto a south-west facing garden designed for total privacy and year-round enjoyment.
Accommodation includes five spacious bedrooms, three of them en suite, a study/library, and two grand reception rooms, each finished to the highest specification. Every detail has been considered — from underfloor heating and designer lighting to the integrated sound system and premium appliances throughout.
A full utility and boiler room, guest WC, and ample storage complement the home’s functionality. The property benefits from secure off-street parking for up to three cars, accessed via remote electric gates, and formal landscaped front and rear gardens with terraces perfectly oriented for afternoon and evening sun.
Located moments from Herbert Park, the Dylan Hotel, and the boutiques, cafés, and restaurants of Ballsbridge and Donnybrook, Wellington Road stands at the very heart of Dublin’s Embassy district — an address synonymous with prestige, privacy, and convenience.
Available immediately for short or long-term lease, this is the first letting of a residence of rare refinement and distinction.

This exceptional home combines classic architectural detail with contemporary style, featuring beautifully proportioned reception rooms, a superb open-plan kitchen and living area at garden level, and five generous bedrooms — three of which include en suite bathrooms. Upstairs, the main bedroom suite enjoys beautiful sash windows overlooking Wellington Road, while four additional bedrooms — two with ensuites — and a luxuriously appointed family bathroom complete the upper accommodation. Perfectly positioned, Pembroke Road ranks among Dublin’s most sought-after addresses. It is within easy walking distance of St. Stephen’s Green and the city’s primary business districts, including the Silicon Docks at Grand Canal. Nearby Herbert Park offers 34 acres of green space for walking, tennis, and relaxation. Excellent shopping, dining, and cafés can be found moments away in Ballsbridge, Baggot Street, and Donnybrook. Prestigious schools, the RDS, Leinster Rugby HQ, and the Aviva Stadium are all within a short stroll, while Dublin Airport is easily accessible via the Port Tunnel. This is a truly special home — elegant, welcoming, and full of character — offering an exceptional opportunity to acquire a period residence in the heart of Dublin 4, with every convenience close at hand.

Description:
Herbert & Lansdowne is delighted to present this stunning, fully furnished, substantially refurbished three-bed, three-bath home on Patrick Street, Dún Laoghaire. With a striking Scandinavian aesthetic, top-tier appliances, and elegant interior design, this 138 m² home blends style, light, and comfort seamlessly.

Entering into an inviting entrance hall, you're drawn into a bright, open-plan living, dining, and kitchen area that flows effortlessly to a small, beautifully landscaped rear garden,  perfect for entertaining or relaxing outdoors. This exceptional home holds a B3 energy rating, reflecting its high-quality insulation and efficiency.

Situated in the heart of Dún Laoghaire, this home enjoys the perfect balance of seaside tranquility and urban convenience. Just a short stroll away are the East and West Piers, People's Park, and the scenic promenade — ideal for walks along Dublin Bay. The town's rich maritime character is reflected in nearby yacht clubs, the Harbour, and a vibrant waterfront atmosphere.

Everyday conveniences are close at hand with George's Street, the Pavilion and Bloomfields Shopping Centres, and an excellent selection of boutiques, cafés, and restaurants all within walking distance. Cultural highlights such as the DLR Lexicon Library and Cultural Centre and the Pavilion Theatre further enhance the appeal of the area.

Public transport connections are superb. The DART provides quick and regular access to Dublin City Centre, while numerous Dublin Bus routes serve the area. The Aircoach also connects Dún Laoghaire directly to Dublin Airport.

Commuting is easy, with the city centre typically reachable in around 25-30 minutes, making Dún Laoghaire an ideal coastal base with exceptional accessibility.

This home offers an elegant, design-forward living experience in one of Dublin's most sought-after seaside towns — combining contemporary comfort, style, and convenience in a truly special setting.

Description:
Earlsfort Court is situated on Hatch Street in Dublin 2, a short walk from St. Stephens Green and Grafton Street. A stylish main bathroom with full sized bath completes the accommodation.

Location 

Tucked away just off Hatch Street in the heart of Dublin 2, 22 Earlsfort Court offers a rare opportunity to enjoy city living at its most convenient. This prime location places you just moments from St Stephen's Green, the Iveagh Gardens, and Grafton Street, with its vast array of shops, cafés, and restaurants.

Whether you're commuting or exploring the city, excellent transport links are right on your doorstep, including the LUAS at Harcourt Street, the DART at Pearse Station, and numerous Dublin Bus routes.
The area is also home to some of Dublin's most iconic cultural and business landmarks, including the National Concert Hall, Iveagh House, and many leading law firms and tech companies. For those who value both lifestyle and location, 22 Earlsfort Court delivers the perfect balance of comfort, convenience, and city charm.

***EMAIL ENQUIRIES ONLY PLEASE****APOLOGIES WE WILL NOT BE IN A POSITION TO RESPOND TO ALL ENQUIRIES****Olivers Estate Agents are delighted to bring to the rental market this spacious three-bedroom semi-detached house, ideally positioned in the highly sought-after residential development of College Park Way, Ballinteer, Dublin 16. Situated within a quiet cul-de-sac and surrounded by mature landscaping, this well-presented home offers bright and spacious accommodation in a prime location, just a short stroll from Dundrum Village and the Dundrum Town Centre.
The property benefits from off-street parking to the front and a private rear garden with patio area, ideal for outdoor dining and entertaining. The accommodation includes a welcoming entrance hallway, a spacious living room with open-plan kitchen and dining area with direct access to the rear garden. Upstairs, there are three bedrooms with built-in wardrobes, including a master bedroom with en-suite bathroom, as well as a main bathroom.
Ballinteer is a highly sought-after residential suburb in South Dublin, known for its excellent location beside Dundrum and its abundance of local amenities. Residents enjoy easy access to the extensive shopping, dining, and entertainment options at Dundrum Town Centre, as well as a wide selection of cafés, bars, and restaurants in the surrounding area. The neighbourhood also offers superb leisure and recreational facilities, including Meadowbrook Leisure Centre, Airfield Estate, and Ballawley Park.
Ballinteer is exceptionally well-connected, with the Dundrum LUAS stop within walking distance, providing swift access to the city centre. Several Dublin Bus routes serve the area, including the L25, 14, 44, 74, and 116, offering convenient links to UCD, Sandyford, Tallaght, and beyond. The nearby M50 motorway further enhances accessibility to all major routes and Dublin Airport
Viewing is highly recommended!
