Title: Daneswell Place, Botanic Road, Glasnevin, Dublin 9, Drumcondra, Dublin 9
Description:
Daneswell Place is a new residential development in an enclosed cul-de-sac development in Glasnevin, Dublin 9. 

These new A-rated apartments are situated just over 2km from the city centre where residents will find city living at its best with numerous cafes, restaurants, bars, supermarkets and shops close by. 

, there is an offering of 2 Bedroom apartments at the same location 
Commuting or just a trip into town is simplicity itself. With walking to IFSC or town taking less than 25 minutes, and cycling even quicker, commutes don't come much more convenient. The area is very well served by public transport too. The Luas takes just 12 minutes from Phibsborough to George's Dock, plus there are also direct bus routes to the City Centre, Rathmines, Grangegorman and Donnybrook from the area or Drumcondra Train Station is a short walk away. If you are heading away, it's a mere 20 minutes (10km) drive from Daneswell Place to Dublin Airport.

All apartments are spacious and fully furnished to a high standard to include a large Smart TV to stream services. High-speed fibre broadband is included in the price for each apartment which is managed by our IT company to ensure there is little or no disruption.

Walking distance to buses, Luas and Drumcondra train station making for an easy commute. 

Heat recovery systems provide a continuous fresh clean filtered air supply for a dust and allergy-free environment for a healthier standard of living. Flexible terms with 12 months or longer agreements but only one month's notice is required if your circumstances change. 

Residents have a private or Juliet balcony, and all apartments have access to a private roof garden with fabulous views over Dublin. 

Car parking and storage for bicycles available.

Features:
- Large kitchen / dining 
- High specification kitchen with integrated Fridge / Freezer, Dishwasher, electric hob and oven and washer / dryer 
- Living Room with large smart screen TV connected to high-speed fibre line to stream services.
- Video intercom system to the main entrance doors and spy hole on apartment doors
- Communal space has CCTV coverage for security
- Individually controlled heating in every room 
- Maintenance on call 
- Modern A-rated energy-efficient apartments 
- Private community in an enclosed cul-de-sac 

Glasnevin is one of Dublin's most historic and long-established communities and, not only does it offer fine parklands and local colleges, but it also has all the amenities and excitement of the city centre less than 25 minutes' walk away. With the perfect mix of contemporary city living and suburban calm, it's no surprise that this neighbourhood is one of the city's most desirable and sought-after locations.

Description:
Introducing an elegant, protected structure in beautiful Blackrock with sea views and easy access to the beach. Located opposite Blackrock College and a stone's throw from Blackrock Hospital. In case you ever choose to leave this beautiful home, you'll find yourself equidistant from Booterstown DART Station and Blackrock DART Station, both only a 5 minute walk away!

There is a roomy back garden with patio, bamboo and  silver birch, and to the front of the house there is a highly coveted parking space!

Title: Majestic Victorian Terrace & Mews, Dartmouth Square, Ranelagh, Dublin 6
Description:
Newly renovated, fully furnished. Available from December 1st.

5SRE - 5 Star Real Estate presents:

Majestic Victorian Terrace & Mews
Circa 1900, this outstanding period residence is an impressive legacy of the architectural elegance and opulence synonymous with Victorian and Edwardian Dublin. Dartmouth Square is perfectly nestled in one of Irelands most sought after and upmarket residences, previously nurturing great artists such as Dubliners songwriter and musician Luke Kelly, Oscar winner Barry Fitzgerald and notable poet Paul Durkan.

Fifty Six is a splendid home and a must for discerning clientele. This red brick two-story over-basement house brims with light, countless features and would greatly appeal to many. It was last renovated in 2024 by the current owners, an architecturally engineered design, laying it out over three levels, seamlessly marrying antiquity and nuevo. There is an optional one-bed mews with its own private entrance to the rear, facing onto sunny Dartmouth Lane. 

Arriving onto the square you are greeted by a boulevard of mature trees.  The front garden is meticulously manicured before ascending onto a beautifully crafted front door.

The entrance hall is laid with stunning polished walnut parquet flooring, complemented by high ceilings and finished with intricate coving that seamlessly flow into the formal interconnecting reception rooms.

The drawing room to the front has two sash windows showcasing a panoramic view of Dartmouth Square. The rooms centerpiece is an elegant brown veined cream marble fire surround with a coal effect gas fire, this perfectly compliments the regal tone while creating warmth and comfort.

Continuing on, the formal dining room showcases a brown marble fireplace with cream veining. Its sash window overlooks the very private and secure sun kissed south facing back garden.

Features:

Brand new to South Dublin's rental market

Panoramic Aspect over Dartmouth Square

Built circa 1900 AD

House - 2600 sq. ft  -  Mews - 350 sq. ft

Highly sought after location & residence

Walking distance to city centre and financial centre

Notable artists, actors & poets lived and still resides on the square

Nestled along the banks of the Grand Canal

Refurbished in late 2024

Title: Neptune House, Temple Crescent, Blackrock, Co. Dublin
Description:
**** Breathtaking Newly Refurbished Penthouse Apartment To Let With Panoramic Views **** 

Dillon Marshall are proud to present this breathtaking three bedroom Penthouse Apartment with Panoramic Views of the Sea. Located in the ever popular Neptune House, This stunning Penthouse apartment boast many original features such as high ceilings, the original stained-glass windows and ornate plaster work. These spacious and newly refurbished apartments have been uniquely designed with well-proportioned rooms, excellent specifications, thoughtful design and of course the highest standards of construction & workmanship.

The original house was built in c.1767 as a private Georgian Residence and was once the home to The Earl of Clonmel, Chief Justice of the King\' s Bench in 1784. In 1916 it was home to British reinforcement troops who landed in Dun Laoghaire for the purpose of defeating the Republican Army at the GPO and during the First World War it was set up as an auxiliary hospital. In 1930 it was opened as a charity for infants known as St Patricks Infants Hospital run by Mary Josephine Cruice.
Neptune House sits between the villages of Blackrock and Monkstown and blends perfectly into the mature surroundings. The houses are contemporary in design and are a visual contrast against the Georgian grandeur of the main house. All houses benefit from the very latest modern efficiencies that A-Rated homes enjoy. The houses employ the latest in modern technologies to achieve their A-rating including a highly efficient heat exchange heating system, state of the art Carlson windows. Internally, each house is fitted to a very high standard with beautiful fitted kitchens and premium integrated appliances, superior tiling, elegant fitted wardrobes and high ceilings at ground floor level.

Situated just 5 miles from Dublin City Centre, Blackrock combines total convenience with a wealth of exceptional amenities. Neptune House is within a short walk of both Blackrock and Monkstown villages hosting an excellent range of shops, churches, seafront walks and an unrivalled range of sports clubs. The DART is very convenient and an abundance of bus routes pass along the Rock Road.

Title: Woodward Heath, Dublin 18, Leopardstown, Dublin 18
Description:
We are delighted to introduce 4 bedroom Semi-detached house in Glencairn Gate. 
An exclusive development of high quality and elegant 4 bedroom NZEB (Near Zero Energy Building) rated house. Situated in Leopardstown, Glencairn gate features mature specimen planting from around the world and stone walls which give a sense character, warmth and homeliness.

Once the site of Murphystown Castle where the legend of Glencairn Gate comes to life. The original house was designed in 1859 by eminent architect Benjamin Woodward. It features a castellated tower, Oriel windows, granite columns and a walled garden. It has been central to Irelands cultural, architectural, and diplomatic history as the British Ambassador' s residence since 1963. Its expansive ' Woodland Park' is now open to the public and should deserves to be visited.

Internally, kitchens are custom designed by O' Connor' s and boast Quartz counter tops and feature over counter lighting, along with high quality integrated appliances comprising an oven, hob, fridge /freezer, dishwasher and microwave. Utility rooms will have fitted storage units and a separate washing machine, dryer and have a tiled floor.

Attractive bathrooms and ensuites will be extensively tiled and come equipped with thermostatically controlled showers and top quality sanitary ware from waterloo bathrooms. Master ensuite and guest WC feature custom made vanity units by Brogan Jordan.

Homes at Glencairn gate are fitted with super-efficient Daikin air to water heat pumps for hot water and thermostatically controlled radiators which can facilitate the installation of the Heatmiser Neo Hub and use of Heatmiser App smart home technology.

Merrion Gardens is a rare jewel: an exclusive, private collection of just eight four-bedroom gated residences, quietly tucked away behind the tree-lined avenues of Merrion Road in Ballsbridge, Dublin 4. Each home has been thoughtfully architect-designed to combine elegance, comfort, and modern living.
This prestigious address offers a true retreat from the bustle of city life while placing you at the heart of all that Dublin has to offer. Within a short stroll are Herbert Park, the Aviva Stadium, the RDS Showgrounds, and Merrion Shopping Centre. Title: Thalassa, Ceanchor Road, Baily, Howth, Dublin 13
Description:
Thalassa has been meticulously refurbished to the highest standard, with every detail thoughtfully designed and executed. The result is one of the most spectacular properties on the market, seamlessly blending luxury, comfort and modern living with an array of smart home features. 

Upon entering the property visitors are welcomed by a grand entrance hallway, setting the tone for the elegance found throughout the home. Facing you from the front door is a sunroom bathed in natural light overlooking Dublin Bay. The expansive kitchen is equipped with state-of-the-art appliances, a walk-in pantry for additional storage, and a dining area enhanced by a hand-crafted bay-window seat. 

From the kitchen, the home flows naturally into the large library—a unique feature of this home. This versatile space can be adapted as a cosy sitting room or a home-office, depending on personal preference. 

There is a Frame TV in situ. At the opposite end of the house, a large reception room is perfectly positioned to maximise the breathtaking south-facing views of the Bay. 

There is also a spacious en-suite bedroom on ground floor, and a visitors’ restroom. Upstairs, there are three en-suite bedrooms. The master suite boasts a luxurious walk-in dressing room and bathroom. Two of the en-suites feature baths, and all four are equipped with top-of-the-range showers. 

The property is surrounded by generous gardens to front and back, offering a serene escape and ample private space. The south-facing aspect ensures the front garden and the granite patio are bathed in sunlight, making them a perfect extension of the home’s living spaces. The smart home system also extends outdoors, with a robot lawnmower keeping the garden pristine year-round. 

Key Features:
• Electric blinds, robot vacuums on both floors, and a robot lawnmower for effortless control and maintenance. 
• Comprehensive security system, including CCTV, for convenience and peace of mind. 
• New wooden floors throughout, with carpeted library, stairs and landing for added comfort. 
• Utility room equipped with a Miele washing machine and dryer. 
• Driveway with ample parking and electric gates. 
• Open fireplace in the reception room and double-sided wall stove fire between hall and kitchen for character and comfort. 
• Modernised electrics, plumbing and insulation for an energy-efficient and contemporary living environment. 
• Fast broadband, CAT6 throughout with meshed WiFi. 

Thalassa is located on the picturesque Howth peninsula, between the villages of Howth and Sutton. The peninsula boasts 16 km of stunning coastline, scenic beaches, and a vibrant marina for boating enthusiasts. The property is conveniently close to some of Ireland's finest golf courses, including those in Portmarnock, The Island and Royal Dublin. Sailing, tennis and field sports are popular locally. 

Howth village offers a delightful selection of fine dining restaurants, boutique cafés and shops. Sutton has a large supermarket and further facilities. The DART line provides a quick and easy commute to Dublin city centre. 

Dublin Airport is approximately a 25-minute drive away. Additionally, there are prestigious schools in close proximity. 

Combining luxurious living with meticulous design, character, cutting-edge technology and a prime location, Thalassa is a one-of-a-kind property perfect for discerning residents seeking an extraordinary home.

Description:
Murphy Moore Property Services Ltd. is proud to present this exceptional A2-rated two-bedroom, two-bathroom apartment to the rental market at No. 4, 17 The Meadow, Robswall, Malahide, Co. Dublin.

This beautifully finished home offers luxury coastal living with the added benefit of low utility bills thanks to its energy-efficient design and newly installed high-speed fibre broadband. Situated in a prestigious development moments from the sea, the apartment combines comfort, style, and convenience.

From the moment you step inside, the attention to detail is evident. The high-end communal hallway features marble flagstone floors and commissioned artwork, setting a refined tone. With only two apartments per floor, each residence enjoys a dual-aspect layout.

Both bedrooms benefit from sea views, while the spacious open-plan kitchen, dining, and living area opens onto a southwest-facing main balcony with a further sea view, overlooking the beautifully landscaped green expanse of Paddy’s Hill. Thoughtful planting offers privacy without compromising the outlook, and the orientation fills the living space with warm evening light — the perfect setting for relaxing at home.

The apartment includes a wide entrance hallway, a generous master bedroom with en-suite shower room, and a second double bedroom — each with built-in wardrobes, plush carpets, and access to its own private balcony with sea views. A separate utility room houses the washing machine, dryer, and hot press, while instant hot water (no immersion system required) provides added everyday convenience.

The property includes one designated parking space, ample visitor parking, and on-street parking in The Meadow. Each apartment is due to receive its own EV charging unit, with installation expected soon. The building also benefits from barrier-free access via a ramp and in-house lift — ideal for buggies or those requiring wheelchair or walker accessibility, an uncommon advantage in the local rental market.

Robswall offers the best of both worlds — just a two-minute stroll to the beach and scenic green spaces of Paddy’s Hill, yet within easy reach of Malahide Village (20-minute walk / five-minute drive), with its excellent array of shops, restaurants, cafés, Malahide Castle, and numerous sports and leisure clubs.

This is a rare opportunity to rent in one of Malahide’s most desirable developments. Early viewing is highly recommended.

Title: 17 Raglan Road, Dublin 4, Ballsbridge, Dublin 4
Description: REA Halnon McKenna are delighted to present this fully restored Victorian property on the corner of raglan Road and Elgin Road, right in the heart of Dublin's embassy belt. Number 17 raglan Road is a stunning, completely refurbished and modernised residence that commands a triple-aspect view, and draws in all available light from every side. Originally built around 1875. Designed & refurbished by John Meagher of de Blacam & Meagher to, and, with help from a top team of professionals, set about this daunting project. The entire building was completely gutted, with internal floors, walls, windows and roofs removed. Given a clean slate, the walls were insulated and double-glazed windows installed, making it one of those rarities: an energy-efficient Victorian home - though it is Ber-exempt. Underfloor heating systems were installed, negating the need for radiators, thus leaving the walls free for furniture and shelving. The house has also been wired for phone, audio, TV and security system, and there's an interior vacuum system, eliminating the hassle of dragging a Hoover around the house. Anything that could be salvaged was lovingly restored, including the original cornicing. Anything that couldn't was replaced with an expertly sourced period piece, including the feature fireplaces and beautiful chandeliers. The five bathrooms and two guest WCs are particularly impressive, all laid out in luxurious marble. A team of Italian craftspeople fitted the bathrooms in Calacatta and Jerusalem Gold marble. In an impressive feat of craftsmanship, all the marble slabs have been near-perfectly bookmatched, with incredible results. The handmade cabinetry in the bathrooms was built by John Daly, and he took up the Italian challenge by bookmatching the grain on the timber. The main entrance has a tiled reception hall with ceiling coving and centre rose, and an inner hall with teak flooring. The large drawingroom and diningroom lead out to a sunroom/winter garden overlooking the rear, with folding doors that can be opened out to create a terrace, and remote-controlled rooflights fitted with rain sensors so they'll automatically close when the weather starts getting a bit Irish. You can imagine hosting elegant receptions, your guests enjoying aperitifs in this elegant space. There's also a large dual-aspect home office/library to the rear that gets lots of light in the afternoon and evening. Downstairs at garden level is a nicely laid out Bulthaup kitchen in a Hampton conservatory, with cantilevered units, large centre island and Gaggenau appliances, including an oven, steam oven and microwave lined up in an impressive row. The glass ceilings allow for all-day light, and the skylights are remote-controlled with rain sensors. It opens to a fully landscaped west-facing garden with cut granite walls and mature planting and hedging. There's an underground rainwater harvesting system that pumps grey water to irrigate the garden. A large family room adjoins the kitchen, and there's a small study/office and two bedrooms, one with en suite. Through an arch on the first-floor return you'll find a bright, dual-aspect bedroom and a bathroom with a large picture window to the side. The first floor is completely taken up with the magnificent dual-aspect main bedroom, with sliding sash picture windows commanding a view over raglan and Elgin roads, along with large walk-in wardrobe and en suite shower room. There's another bedroom suite on the third floor, along with a small room on the second-floor return that could work as a laundry/ironing room, a small study/office, or simply a handy storage space. Outside there's off-street parking for two (large) cars, accessed through electric sliding gates to the side. There's also a handy side entrance for convenient access in and out.

Title: 24 Leeson Park, Ranelagh, Dublin 6
Description:
This elegant house is located in the heart of Dublin in the Upper Leeson Street/Dartmouth Square neighbourhood straddling Dublin 4 and 6. within a 10 minute walk from St Stephens Green. Comprising of elegant Victorian houses, Leeson Park is home to a number of Embassies and Ambassador’s residences. This southern section of the city is home to numerous Tech companies (Google, Linkdin etc). It is a quiet tree lined road, with little traffic and with easy access, on foot and with public transport to the city centre. Bus connections closeby to University College Dublin, Trinity College Dublin, Heuston Rail Station and Dublin Airport. Within 5 minute’s walk there are 6 neighbourhood restaurants, a Pub, a Spar supermarket and a Launderette. The Clayton Burlington Hotel is also a 5 minute walk from Leeson Park. Luas Station 7 minute walk. Ranelagh Village, with its shops, restaurants, bars and supermarkets is a 10 minute walk. City Bikes for hire closeby. Numerous Primary and Secondary schools nearby within easy reach on foot or by public transport.

This tastefully decorated 2,900 sqft house comprises three floors with front entrances on Garden level and Main Entrance Floor Level, up granite steps. On the Entrance Level floor there are two elegant and bright high ceiling interconnecting reception rooms (sitting and dining rooms). Also at the rear on Entrance Level is a newly installed fully equipped kitchen with access to the southwest orientated garden via outside steps. On the Upper Floor and return there are 4 double bedrooms, one of which is the Master bedroom with adjoining private ensuite bathroom. One of the other bedrooms also contains its own ensuite WC and shower room. At Garden Level there is a fully equipped kitchen, continuous with the spacious living area opening onto the sunny garden, a bathroom and a Bedroom/Home Office. Off street and on street parking is available at the front of the house. At the rear of the house there is a spacious garage opening onto Northbrook Lane.


Amenities
Kitchen - Dishwasher, Gas Hob, Electric Oven and grill, Microwave, Refrigerator and Fridge Freezer, washing machine, Capsule coffee machine.
Other Amenities available- WiFi, TV, Iron, Cable TV.
